a Kommentre','KOMMENT TARTALMA'),('portal.createwf.wflist1','Create WF from Graph Comment','This radio button must be selected if the user wants to create a new <strong>workflow</strong> from an existing <strong>Graph</strong> defining it as its skeleton. <br /> Each feature of the new workflow must be defined during the later configuration phase(s).<br /> To configurate the created workflow the proper list element of the <em><strong>Workflow/Concrete</strong></em> tab must be selected.<br /> <br />'),('portal.createwf.wflist2','Create WF from Template Comment','This radio button must be selected if the user wants to create a new<strong> workflow</strong> using an existing <strong>Template</strong> presetting the Graph and some not changeable features of the Workflow.<br /> The changeable features of the new workflow can be defined during the later configuration phase(s).<br /> To configure the created workflow the proper list element of the <u><em><strong>Workflow/Concrete</strong></em></u> tab must be selected.'),('Portal.createwf.wflist3','Create WF from Workflow Comment','This radio button must be selected if the user wants to create a new <strong>workflow</strong> by copying an existing one.<br />The changeable features of the new workflow can be (re)defined during the later configuration phase(s).<br />To configure the created workflow the proper list element of the <u><em><strong>Workflow/Concrete</strong></em></u> tab must be selected.<br />A feature will not be changeable if the original workflow had been restricted by a <strong>Template</strong>, and the given feature was marked as fixed there.'),('portal.createwf.wfname','Create WF new Name','A name must be defined for the new <strong>workflow</strong>. This name must be unique in the namespace of the workflows of the given user. <br /> &nbsp;The name may contain alphanumerical characters, white space, dash(-) and underline(_) characters.<br /> <em>At the moment the <strong>workflows</strong> and the <strong>Templates</strong>&nbsp; of the given user have a common namespace.</em>'),('portal.createwf.wfdesc','Create WF Note comment','The user can place free text here. This will appear next to the <strong>workflow</strong> entry on the Workflow/Concrete list.<br /> The default value of this field is the date of the creation of the workflow.'),('portal.template.wflist1','Create Template  base WF comment','When selecting this radio button the full list of existing <strong>workflows</strong> are accessible and one can serve as the base of the <strong>template generation</strong>. Each <strong>feature</strong> of the selected workflow can be set later as <strong>free</strong> or <strong>closed</strong>.<br /> If later the user defines a new workflow with the help of a <strong>template</strong>, only the free features will be reconfigurable.<br /> <br />'),('portal.template.wflist2','Create Template  base WF derived comment','This radio button must be selected in the special case to access a restricted list of existing <strong>workflows</strong>.<br /> This list contains only those workflows, which have been created referencing a named <strong>Template</strong>.<br /> Consequently the selectable workflow may have some already &ldquo;<strong>closed</strong>&rdquo; features. These features remain closed during the current template definition process.'),('portal.template.newname','Create Template new Template Name Comment','<p>A name must be defined for the new <strong>template</strong>.This name must be unique in the namespace of the templates of the given user. <br />The name may contain alphanumerical characters, white space, dash(-) and underline(_) characters.</p><p><br /><em>At the moment the <strong>workflows</strong> and the <strong>templates</strong> of the given user have a common namespace.</em></p>'),('Portal.template.desc','Create Template Note Comment','<p>The user can place free text here. <br />This will appear next to the <strong>template</strong> name in the list on the <u><em><strong>Workflow/Template</strong></em></u> tab.<br />The default value of this field is the date of the creation of the template.</p><p><strong>This field must not be empty</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p>'),('workflowgraf.delete.ok','Java_graph_deleted_ok','The graph has been deleted'),('workflowgraf.delete.error','Java_graph_deleted_err','Internal error at the attempt to delete the graph.<br />( Service access error or programming error)'),('portal.RealWorkflowPortlet.doSubmit','Java_wf_submit_started','The workflow has been submitted'),('template.delete.ok','Java_template_deleted_ok','The template has been deleted'),('template.delete.error','Java_template_deleted_err','Internal error at the attempt to delete the template.<br />( Service access error or programming error)'),('template.workflow.exist','Java_template_name_exist','The template name already exist'),('template.desc.notset','Java_template_note_not_set','The <strong>optional note</strong> field cannot be left empty'),('template.name.notset','Java_template_name_not_set','Attempt to create a template without a <strong>Name</strong>'),('workflow.template.created','Java_template_created','The template has been created successfully'),('portal.TimingWorkflowPortlet.delete','Java_timeing_delete','<p>The workflow has been revoked from schedule list</p>'),('portal.TimingWorkflowPortlet.add','Java_timeing_add','The workflow will be started at the defined time'),('portal.TimingWorkflowPortlet.notime','Java_timeing_time_problem','<p>Defined submission time is less than the current time displayed as <strong>Reference server time</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>'),('portal.TimingWorkflowPortlet.noadd','Java_timeing_error','The workflow is already in the schedule list, do not duplicate'),('portal.newWorkflow.noname','Java_workflow_name_not_set','Attempt to create a workflow without a <strong>Name</strong>'),('portal.newWorkflow.nodesc','Java_workflow_note_not_set','The <strong>optional note</strong> field cannot be left empty'),('portal.newWorkflow.nocreate','Java_workflow_name_exist','The workflow name already exists<br />'),('portal.newWorkflow.create','Java_workflow_created','The workflow has been created successfully'),('portal.newWorkflow.noparent','Java_workflow_create_err_father','No base (Graph, Template, other Workflow) has been defined at the attempt to create a new workflow'),('portal.newWorkflow.error','Java_workflow_create_err','Internal error during the attempt to create a new Workflow<br />(for example network communication error)'),('portal.timing.wflist','Timeing_WF_list','An existing <strong>workflow</strong> can be selected in order to put it in the <strong>Schedule Table</strong> with a <strong>Submission time</strong>.<br />The submission time must not be less than the shown <strong>Reference server time</strong>.<br />Following the submission the given entry will be deleted from the Schedule Table. <br />'),('portal.timing.year','Timeing_year','Year of submission.<br />The submission time must not be less than the shown Reference server time.<br />'),('portal.timing.month','Timeing_month','Month of submission.<br />The submission time must not be less than the shown Reference server time.<br />'),('portal.timing.day','Timeing_day','Day of submission.<br />The submission time must not be less than the shown Reference server time.<br />'),('portal.timing.hour','Timeing_hour','Hour of submission.<br />The submission time must not be less than the shown Reference server time.<br />'),('portal.timing.minute','Timeing_minute','Minute of submission.<br />The submission time must not be less than the shown Reference server time.<br />'),('portal.remote.wflist','Remote_WF_list','An existing <strong>workflow</strong> can be selected in order to put it in the <strong>Event Listener Table.</strong><br />An external program of a remote client can awake the listener and trigger the submission of the defined workflow.<br />The listening works as a <strong>Web Service</strong>.<br />The external program must use the <strong>WSDL</strong> protocol. &nbsp;<br />The accurate form of the WSDL protocol is described in a separate document.<br />'),('Portal.remote.keytext','Remote_WF_key','A secret alphanumerical key must be defined here.<br />The remote process which awakes the listener to submit the requested <strong>workflow</strong> must identify itself by sending the key which will be checked against the value stored here.<br />'),('portal.wfupload.upfilename','Upload_file_name_comment','The name of a locally stored existing compressed file can be defined here.<br />The file must contain the definition of a <strong>workflow</strong> (eventually with its instances) which has been previously downloaded from the Portal server to the local environment by any of the commands of the <u><em><strong>Workflow/Storage</strong></em></u> tab.<br />The proper parts of the workflow will be added to the respecting lists (<em><strong>Graph</strong></em>, <em><strong>Template</strong></em>, <em><strong>Concrete</strong></em>).<br />To avoid name collisions the user can rename the parts.<br />'),('portal.wfupload.graf','Upload_graph_change_comment','By setting the checkbox the user indicates the intention to rename the <strong>graph</strong> part of the object to be uploaded.'),('portal.wfupload.abst','Upload_template_change_comment','By setting the checkbox the user indicates the intention to rename the <strong>template</strong> part of the object to be uploaded. <br />'),('portal.wfupload.real','Upload_workflow_change_comment','By setting the checkbox the user indicates the intention to rename the <strong>workflow</strong> part of the object to be uploaded.'),('portal.wfimport.wftype','Import_wftype_comment','<p>The user can select the <strong>type</strong> of the <strong>repository item</strong> which will be <strong>imported</strong> or <strong>deleted</strong>.<br />The repository is a shared storage between the users to assist collaboration.<br />The types are the followings: <br /><strong><br />Application:</strong> <br />Contains a tested concrete <em><strong>workflow</strong></em>. <br />An application must contain the definition(s) of the <em><strong>embedded (called) workflows</strong></em> as well. Mostly the input files or the resources of the imported application can be reconfigured.<br />The objects of the embedded workflows will have a local namespace so they need no renaming.<br /><br /><strong>Projects: </strong><br />Same as <em><strong>Application</strong></em> with the difference that the <strong><em>workflow</em></strong> do not need to be complete and each <strong><em>feature</em></strong> is set to <strong>free</strong> and can be reconfigured. It should be noted that a <strong>project</strong> differs from a <em><strong>concrete workflow</strong></em> because a <strong>project</strong> may contain the definition(s) of the <em><strong>embedded workflow(s).</strong></em></p><p><strong>Concrete Workflows:</strong><br />Single <em><strong>workflow</strong></em> which must contain additionally a <em><strong>Graph</strong></em> definition and may contain a <strong>Template</strong> definition.</p><p><strong>Template:</strong><br />This must contain additionally a <strong><em>Graph</em></strong> definition.<br /><br /><strong>Graph:</strong></p>'),('portal.wfimport.executetype','Import_wftype_execute_comment','The user can select between two commands before applying <strong>execute</strong> on the marked object. <br />The marking must have been done on the <strong>refreshed list</strong> of objects of the selected <strong>type</strong>. &nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>Import:</strong><br />The proper parts of the <strong>workflow</strong> will be added to the respecting lists (<em><strong>Graph</strong></em>, <em><strong>Template</strong></em>, <em><strong>Concrete</strong></em>).<br />To avoid name collisions the user can rename the parts. <br />(Remember that the objects of the <strong>embedded workflows</strong> &ndash;in case of <strong>Applications</strong>, and <strong>Projects</strong> - do not need to be renamed because their namespace is local to the main <strong>workflow</strong>)<br />The import differs from the <em><strong>Workflow/Upload</strong></em> because it is a &ldquo;from <strong>server</strong> to <strong>server</strong>&rdquo; operation and not a &ldquo;from <strong>local</strong> to <strong>server</strong>&rdquo; one. <br /><br /><strong>Delete:</strong><br />Deletes the object from the shared repository of the portal users. <br />'),('portal.wfimport.graf','Import_graph_change_comment','By setting the checkbox the user indicates the intention to rename the <strong>graph</strong> part of the object to be imported.'),('portal.wfimport.abst','Import_template_change_comment','By setting the checkbox the user indicates the intention to rename the <strong>template</strong> part of the object to be imported.'),('portal.wfimport.real','Import_workflow_change_comment','By setting the checkbox the user indicates the intention to rename the <strong>workflow</strong> part of the object to be imported'),('config.job.gridtype','Config_Job_destination','<p>The <strong>Type</strong> list enumerates the available types of the <strong>submitters</strong> which serve as the backend of the <strong>Portal system</strong>, i.e. they are the sources of the <strong>destinations(Grids)</strong> the binary <strong>jobs</strong> are delivered to.<br />The applicability of finer subordination of the destinations (<strong>Grid</strong>, <strong>Resource/Broker</strong>, <strong>Job manager</strong>) is depending on the actual type.<br />The actual <strong>destinations(Grids)</strong> are listed on the <em><strong>Settings</strong></em> tab and may be manipulated only by the <em>System Administrator</em>.<br />The <em>System Administrator</em> sets the connected <strong>destinations (Grids)</strong> into <strong>Types</strong>. The set of currently existing <strong>Type</strong> names appear in the list. </p><p>More precisely, the appearing list of <strong>Types</strong> depend on the <strong>GRID configurations</strong> listed on the <strong><em>Settings</em></strong> tab which is set by the <em>System Administrator</em>. It might be a bit misleading when the root user adds a new <strong>Grid configuration</strong>, filling the input field &ldquo;<strong>Grid</strong>&rdquo; which originally was used to indicate to which Grid the server of the eventual information system will be associated to. <br />&nbsp;</p><p>For the individual selections of these <strong>Types</strong> the following dedicated conventions are maintained: <br /><strong>gmlca :</strong><br />Is a special service where the <strong>binary</strong> code (legacy code) can be found. It is already on the <strong>destination</strong> system and only the input/output parameters must be delivered between the <strong>Portal</strong> and the <strong>destination</strong>;<br /><strong>Unibroker:</strong><br />Have learned the defined requirements of the <strong>job</strong>. The <strong>meta broker</strong> of the <strong>Portal server</strong> decides to which <strong>destination (Grid)</strong> can be the <strong>job</strong> optimally submitted;<br /><strong>GT-4:</strong><br />In the subordinated <strong>Grid</strong> list only destinations of middleware technology <strong>Globus Toolkit 4</strong> will appear;<br /><strong>GT-2:</strong><br />In the subordinated <strong>Grid</strong> list only destinations of middleware technology <strong>Globus Toolkit 2</strong> will appear;<br /><strong>LCG2:</strong><br />In the subordinated <strong>Grid</strong> list only destinations of middleware technology <strong>LCG2</strong> will appear;<br /><strong>gLite:</strong><br />In the subordinated <strong>Grid</strong> list only destinations of middleware technology <strong>gLite</strong> will appear;<br /><strong>Local:</strong><br />It is an example for special <strong>submitters</strong> enabling to submit <strong>jobs</strong> in a non standard environment. In the current implementation, the infrastructure of the <strong>Portal server</strong> is used as a destination to submit <strong>jobs</strong>. The <em>System Administrator</em> has the potential to add new submitters and destination backend infrastructures to the system at any time. </p>'),('config.job.grid','Config_job_grid','<p>If one of the following had been chosen from the <strong>Type</strong> list, <strong>GT-4</strong>, <strong>GT-2</strong>, <strong>LCG2</strong>, <strong>gLite</strong>, the available <strong>destinations (Grids)</strong> of the selected technology (<strong>Type</strong>) are listed to select from.</p><p>In case of the choice of <strong>Local</strong> as a <strong>Type</strong>, the direct <strong>resources</strong> associated to the <strong>local submitter</strong> by the <em>System Administrator</em> are listed and are selectable.<br /></p><p>&nbsp;</p>'),('config.job.resource','Config_job_resource','If one of the following had been chosen from the <strong>Type</strong> list, <strong> GT-4</strong>, <strong>GT-2</strong>, <strong>LCG2</strong>, <strong>gLite</strong>, the <strong>resource</strong> list belonging to the selected <strong>destination (Grid)</strong> is displayed to select from.<br />The <strong>resource</strong> may be a single <strong>host </strong>or - more frequently - a <strong>Cluster</strong> (pool of hosts) where the delivered <strong>job</strong> will run. <br />The <strong>resources</strong> must have been connected to the respecting <strong>Grid</strong> in the <u><em><strong>Settings</strong></em></u> tab.<br />The special resource name <strong>BROKER</strong> is distinguished if one of the following had been set as <strong>Type</strong>: <strong>LCG2</strong>, <strong>gLite</strong>.<br />In case of the selection of <strong>broker</strong>, the resource broker of the selected <strong>Grid</strong> decides about the <strong>destination</strong> of the <strong>job</strong>.'),('config.job.jobmanager','Config_job_jobmanager','If one of the following had been chosen from the <strong>Type</strong> list, <strong>GT-2</strong>, <strong>LCG2</strong>, <strong>gLite</strong> and the resource is not set to <strong>broker</strong> (which means that the job is directed to a dedicated <strong>resource</strong>), the list of available <strong>job managers</strong> are displayed to select from.<br />The <strong>job manager</strong> gives additional information to schedule a <strong>job</strong> on a dedicated <strong>resource</strong>, and basically means the type of the input <strong>queues</strong>. <br />The <strong>job</strong> can be put into one of these <strong>queue</strong>s to wait to be executed. Each of these <strong>queues</strong>&rsquo; <strong>priorities</strong> to access the computing resources are different. The <strong>priority</strong> associated to the <strong>queue</strong> which contains <strong>short</strong> <strong>jobs</strong> is higher than the <strong>priority</strong> ordered to the <strong>queue</strong>s containing <strong>long jobs</strong> which should run in the background. <br />The <strong>job manager</strong> is defined together with a <strong>resource</strong> when it is connected to the chosen <strong>Grid</strong> in the <u><em><strong>Settings</strong></em></u> tab. <br />It follows that shared <strong>resources</strong> with different <strong>job managers</strong> can be defined.<br />'),('config.job.usealljob','Config_job_usealljobs','If the checkbox is set the current values of <strong>Type</strong>, <strong>Grid</strong>, <strong>Resource/Broker</strong> and <strong>JobManager</strong> will be copied to all of the jobs of the workflow.'),('config.job.type','Config_job_binary_type','<p>Either a translated<strong> binary</strong> or a <strong>Java jar</strong> or a translated <strong>MPI</strong> code can be selected.</p><p>In the case of <strong>Java</strong> selected, the system submits the user defined <strong>jar</strong> file &ndash;for example <em>HelloWorld.jar</em> - using the following the command:<br /> <br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>java &ndash;jar</strong> <em>HelloWorld.jar</em><br /><br />A short example how to generate the <strong>jar</strong> file:<br /><br />1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Edit the proper file - for example <em>Main.java</em> - as <br /> <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>public class Main {&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; public static void main(String[] args)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; { System.out.println(&quot;helloWorld!&quot;); } }</strong></p><p>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Translate the file as <strong>javac</strong> <em>Main.java</em></p><p>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Edit the manifest file <em>MANIFEST.MF</em> to define starter class. In our case as<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>MainClass:Main</strong><br /><br />4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pack the class files and the manifest file together with the selected <u>destination</u> name as<br /><br /><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; jar cmf</strong> <em>MANIFEST.MF</em> <u><em>HelloWorld.jar</em></u> <em>Main.class </em></p>'),('config.job.nodenumber','Config_job_MPI_nodnumber','The number of processors required by the MPI code. This input field can and must be defined only if <strong><em>MPI</em></strong> is selected as <strong>Kind of binary</strong>.'),('config.job.binary','Config_job_binary','The <u><em><strong>File browser</strong></em></u> must be used to define the path of a local file to be uploaded as an <strong>executable binary code</strong> of the <strong>job</strong>.<br />For safety reasons no direct filling of the input field is permitted.<br />The <strong>code</strong> will be delivered upon <strong>job submission</strong> to the proper <strong>resource</strong>.<br />The execution of the <em>upload </em>operation must be prepared in two steps:<br />1. The hitting of the <u><em><strong>save</strong></em> </u> button confirms the <strong>Job</strong> related settings on this page.<br />2. The hitting of the <u><em><strong>Save and Upload</strong></em></u> button starts the workflow level upload operations.<br />The name of the uploaded file is rewritten as argument of the message <em><strong>Recently stored</strong></em>. <br />'),('config.job.params','Config_job_params','The command line parameters intended to be digested upon the execution of the <strong>binary code</strong> and can be defined here.'),('portal.jdlrsl.command','Config_job_jdlrsl_command','A&nbsp;&nbsp; Job Description Language (<strong>JDL</strong>) command can be added to the job, to assist the <em>Broker</em>. <br />This option can be selected only if the <strong>job</strong> is <strong>binary</strong> and the selected <em>destination</em> has a broker and it understands the JDL/RSL, <br />i.e. the value of job Type is GT-4, LCG2 or gLite.&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />'),('portal.jdlrsl.command','Config_job_jdlrsl_command','A&nbsp;&nbsp; Job Description Language (<strong>JDL</strong>) command can be added to the <strong>job</strong> to assist the <em>Broker</em>. <br />This option can be selected only if the <strong>job</strong> is <strong>binary</strong> and the selected destination has a <em>Broker</em> and it understands the <strong>JDL/RSL</strong>, <br />i.e. the value of <strong>job</strong> <strong>Type</strong> is <strong>GT-4</strong>, <strong>LCG2 </strong>or <strong>gLite</strong>.'),('portal.jdlrsl.value','Config_job_jdlrsl_value','This text field can be written if a valid <strong>JDL/RSL</strong> <strong>Command</strong> had been selected from the <em>list box</em> above.<br />The Portal Server makes no syntax check just forwards <strong>JDL/RSL</strong> file to the <em>Broker</em>. Errors reported back after <strong>job submission</strong> among the error messages belonging to the given <strong>job</strong> of a <strong>Workflow instance</strong>.<br />Hitting the <strong>Add</strong> button connects the defined <em>command - value pair</em> to the JDL/RSL.<br />In case of an existing <em>pair</em> the <strong>Command</strong> selector opens the <strong>Value</strong> of the selected item for editing. &nbsp;<br />With defining an empty string as value &ndash;confirmed by the <u><em><strong>Add</strong></em></u> button&ndash; deletes the pair. <br />However it will be visible just after the execution of the workflow level but after hitting the <u><em><strong>Save and Upload</strong></em></u> button the whole <em>pair</em> must disappear from the list of valid pairs listed as &quot;<strong>Actual values</strong>&quot; on the right hand side of the text field.'),('config.input.internalfilename','Config_job_port_input_internalfilename','This string value may be referenced in the <strong>executable</strong> of the <strong>Job</strong> to open a <strong>file</strong> assumed to be present in the working directory (or relative to the working directory) of the <strong>host</strong> where the <strong>job</strong> will be executed. &nbsp;<br />In the simplest case it will be the <strong>name</strong> of the delivered <strong>file</strong> in the destination environment.<br />Certainly it can be a <strong>path</strong> relative to the working directory of the destination environment as well.<br />The default value of the <strong>internal file name</strong> associated to the given <strong>port</strong> of the <strong>job</strong> is inherited from the proper &ldquo;<strong>Port Name</strong>&rdquo; of the <strong>Graph</strong> which have been defined by the <strong>Graph Editor</strong> callable in the  <u><em><strong>Workflow/Graph</strong></em></u> tab<br />'),('config.input.depend','Config_job_port_view_input_cond','The <strong>View</strong> setting allows the editing of the <strong>port</strong> dependent <em>conditions</em> to permit/exclude the running of the <strong>job</strong>.<br />The <strong>input value</strong> delivered through the<strong> port</strong> must be convertible to a <em>string</em>&nbsp; and this will be matched against the <strong>other argument (</strong>which must be a <strong>direct value</strong> or the <strong>content </strong>of a different input <strong>port) using the defined <strong>operator</strong> .</strong> If the comparison returns &nbsp; <strong>false</strong>, it prohibits the submission&nbsp; of the<strong> job</strong>.&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />'),('config.input.equaltype','Config_job_port_input_cond_op','Defines the <strong>Boolean</strong> <strong>operator</strong> to compare the <em>arguments</em>. <br />The <em>first argument</em> is the value delivered by the current <strong>port</strong>.<br />The <em>second argument</em> is selectable with the radio button. <br />The non trivial operator <strong>container</strong> is <strong>true</strong> if the <em>second argument</em> defined here is a substring of the <em>first argument</em>.<br />The other selectable operators <strong>==</strong> , <strong>!=</strong> yield <strong>true</strong>, if the arguments are <u><em>equals</em></u>, <u><em>not equals</em></u> respectively.'),('config.input.equalvalue','Config_job_port_input_arg2_value','The <em>second argument</em> of the comparison operator is a direct value which must be defined in the input field.'),('config.input.pequalinput','Config_job_port_input_arg2_otherport','The <em>second argument</em> of the comparison operator should be the value delivered by a (possibly foreign) input <strong>port</strong> of the <strong>job</strong>. This <strong>port</strong> is selected by the <strong>port number.</strong>'),('config.input.externalname','Config_job_port_input_stored_filename','Displays the <strong>name</strong> of the recently defined <strong>input file</strong>.<br />The accurate <em>source</em> (<strong>local path</strong> or <strong>URL</strong>) of the <strong>input file</strong> can be found in the <u><em><strong>Job Configuration History</strong></em></u> tab.<br />If the recent source of the input was not a <strong>file</strong> but a <strong>direct value</strong> or the result set of an <strong>SQL query,&nbsp;</strong> the default value <strong>N/A</strong>, meaning &ldquo;<strong>not available</strong>&rdquo; will be displayed.<br />The genuine update of the input settings is performed after issuing the <strong>workflow</strong> level <u><em><strong>Save and Upload</strong></em></u> command. The <strong>workflow</strong> level update can be reached after the confirmation of the <strong>job</strong> level update by hitting the <u><em><strong>OK</strong></em></u> button'),('config.input.file','Config_job_port_input_local','<p>Upload a<strong> local file</strong> from the client&rsquo;s computer<br />The file <u><em><strong>Browser</strong></em></u> must be used to define the <em>path</em> of a local file to be uploaded.<br />For safety reasons no direct filling of the input&nbsp; field is permitted.<br />The content of the<strong> file</strong> will be delivered upon job submission to the proper<em> destination</em>.<br /><br />The execution of the upload operation must be prepared in two steps:<br />1. The hitting of the <u><em><strong>OK</strong></em></u> button confirms the <strong>Job</strong> related settings&nbsp; on this page.<br />2. The hitting of the <u><em><strong>Save and Upload</strong></em></u> button starts the <strong>workflow</strong> level <em>upload</em> operations.<br />The name of the uploaded file is rewritten as argument of the message <strong>Recently defined External File Name:</strong></p><p>In the special case when the <strong>input file</strong> will be used&nbsp; as container of several&nbsp; input files for a <strong>Parametric Sweep (PS) </strong>input <strong>port</strong>, the following rules must be observed:<br />1. The uploaded container <strong>file</strong> must have a standard name &ldquo;<strong>paramInputs.zip</strong>&rdquo;<br />2. Its member files must be named as subsequent integer numbers started from &ldquo;<strong>0</strong>&rdquo;. </p>'),('config.input.value','Config_job_port_input_value','The <em>content</em> of the input field will be delivered as a <strong>file</strong> to the working directory of the node executing the <strong>job</strong>.<br />Its name will be a user defined one; identical with the input field of the <strong>Input port&rsquo;s Internal Filename</strong>.'),('config.input.remote','Config_job_port_input_remote','The <strong>URL</strong> of a <strong>remote file</strong> (or of a <strong>remote directory</strong> in case of a <strong>Parameter Sweep port</strong>) must be defined. The URL must have a <em>protocol prefix</em><strong> lfn</strong> or <strong>gsiftp</strong>.<br /><br /><strong>1.</strong> <strong>Simple file case &ndash; not PS port:</strong><br /><br /><strong><em>1.1 prefix</em> </strong><strong>lfn</strong>:<br />The prefix <strong>lfn</strong>: will be used in case of &ldquo;high&rdquo; level <strong>remote file</strong> definition, when the <strong>URL</strong> refers to a <em>logical</em> name according to the convention of the <strong>LFC Grid File Catalogue</strong>. The corresponding&nbsp; ENVIRONMENT variables&nbsp; are set by the system for each <strong>Virtual Organizations</strong> supporting the <strong>LFC</strong> catalogues.<br />At the moment this setting is done in script files handled by the <strong>System Administrator</strong>.<br /><br />The user has two possibilities with the <strong>remote files</strong> defined by the <strong>lfn</strong> like logical name:<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a. Use it as a shared <strong>file</strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; b. Use it as a big remote<strong> file</strong><br />In case (a) the user sets the checkbox <u><em><strong>Copy to WN</strong></em></u>, the system will automatically copy&nbsp; the whole content of the <strong>remote file</strong> to the <strong>Working Node</strong> where the user&rsquo;s <strong>job</strong> will run&nbsp; and the new <strong>file</strong> will be put in the working directory of the <strong>WN</strong> as the user has defined it in&nbsp; <strong>Input port&rsquo;s Internal Filename</strong>. i.e. the user can open the copied<strong> file</strong> traditionally within its <strong>executable</strong>.<br />In case (b) it is the responsibility of the user to link the <em>remote access api</em> &ndash; for example <strong>GFAL</strong> &ndash; to the <strong>executable</strong> code in order to open and fetch the <strong>remote files</strong> through it.&nbsp; The big advantage of this method is that in one time only a fraction of the whole <strong>file</strong> must be copied to the <strong>Working Node</strong>.<br /><em>1.2 prefix</em> <strong>gsiftp</strong>:<br />The prefix <strong>gsiftp</strong>: will be used if the <strong>remote file</strong> is implemented as a shared<strong> file</strong> stored in the local file system of a <strong>remote host</strong>&nbsp; accessible by a <strong>GT2</strong> infrastructure. It&rsquo;s a low level access and the whole file will be copied to the <strong>Working Node</strong> (similar to the case 1.1.a)<br />If the direct copy from the remote file system to the Working Node is not possible because of firewall problems, the system tries to use the <strong>Portal Server</strong> as relay. &nbsp;<br /><br />&nbsp;<strong>2 . Multiple file case&nbsp; - Parameter Sweep PS port:</strong><br />Instead of&nbsp; <strong>file</strong> reference, a <strong>directory</strong> reference must be used in the <strong>URL.</strong><br />This directory must reference members with a common name convention:&nbsp; <em>common prefix</em> terminated by &ldquo;<strong>-</strong>&ldquo; character and a <em>postfix</em> of subsequent integer numbers starting from &ldquo;<strong>0</strong>&rdquo;. &nbsp;<br /><br />'),('config.input.sql','Config_job_port_input_sql_group','<p>The <em>result set</em> of the <strong>SQL Select</strong> command will be the base of the <strong>file</strong> generation.<br />From each member of the <strong>result set</strong> a separate <strong>file</strong> will be built, and forwarded to the destination,&nbsp; identified by the name that the user has defined in the input field of the&nbsp; <strong>Input port&rsquo;s Internal Filename</strong>.</p><p><br />Details of the definition:</p><p><strong>SQL URL:</strong> is the definition of the database where the SELECT command will run. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; It must have the following form:<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>JDBC:</strong>&amp;lt;subprotocol&amp;gt;://&amp;lt;host&amp;gt;:&amp;lt;port&amp;gt;/&amp;lt;Database_name&amp;gt; </p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; where the&nbsp; &amp;lt;subprotocol&amp;gt; is vendor dependent<br /><strong>USER:</strong> is the owner of the Database<br /><strong>Password:</strong> is the security key<br /><strong>SQL Query:</strong> is the argument of the SELECT command.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Make sure that do not terminate the command with a semicolon&nbsp;</p>'),('button.attach','Button_Graph_attach','Edit'),('button.download','Button_Graph_download','Download'),('button.export','Button_Graph_export','Export'),('button.refresh','Button_Graph_refresh','Refresh'),('button.opengrapheditor','Button_Graph_Open_Graph_Editor','Graph Editor'),('config.input.paraminput','Config_job_port_input_Parametric_Details','Selecting <strong>View</strong>,<strong> </strong>the given <strong>input port</strong> can be changed to be a <strong>Parametric Input Port</strong>, where the <em>parametric features</em> can be defined.<br />If this <strong>port</strong> is a <strong>Genuine Input port </strong>&ndash;which means that no <strong>output port</strong> of other <strong>job</strong> is associated to it &ndash; the user can define (as <strong>Input numbers</strong>) how many times the<strong> port</strong> &ldquo;senses&rdquo; a new <strong>input file</strong>. <br />This number will take part in the determination of how many times the <strong>Job</strong> will be <strong>executed</strong>.<br />The default value of it is <strong>1</strong>, which means that the <strong>port</strong> is <em>not a parametric </em>one.<br />If the actual number of files associated to the port differs from the value of the value in the <strong>Input numbers</strong> field, the encountering of <strong>files</strong> upon later <strong>job submissions</strong> will be repeated* / skipped&nbsp; depending on whether the number of<strong> files</strong> is less/greater than the value of <strong>Input numbers</strong>.<br />If this <strong>port</strong> is a <strong>channel port</strong> &ndash; which means that it is fed by the<strong> output port</strong> of an other <strong>job</strong>, then the number of <strong>files</strong> yielded through the channel determine the value of the &ldquo;<strong>Input numbers</strong>&rdquo;.<br />That is the reason why the <strong>Input numbers</strong> may not be defined explicitly in case of <strong>channel</strong> ports i.e. its value is inherited from the <strong>output port </strong>of the preceding <strong>job</strong>. <br />-------*<br />According to the algorithm defined at &ldquo;<strong>Exception at exhausted input</strong>&rdquo;&nbsp;'),('config.input.dpid','Config_job_port_input_Parametric_dpid','The value of the <strong>Port group identifier</strong> (<strong>PID</strong>)&nbsp; will be associated to each <strong>port</strong>.<br /><strong>PID</strong> is used to determine the sets of the so called&nbsp; <strong>Cross Product Group</strong>s<strong> </strong>(<strong>CPG</strong>s) of the job.<br />The <strong>ports</strong> having the same <strong>PID</strong> value belong to the same <strong>CPG</strong>.<br />The default <strong>PID</strong> values are the <strong>port identifiers</strong>, so <em><strong>initially</strong></em> each <strong>port</strong> belongs to a separate <strong>CPG</strong> element.<br /><br />The number of <strong>job submissions</strong> are calculated upon the investigation of existing <strong>CPG</strong>s:<br />&nbsp;1. A <strong>CPG</strong> determines all the possible <strong>file</strong> combinations of its member <strong>Port</strong>s, where a member port defines as many <strong>file</strong>s as the value of its <strong>Input number</strong>s are. Shortly speaking the cardinality of a <strong>CPG</strong> is the <em><strong>Descartes product</strong></em> of the <strong>Input numbers</strong> of its members.<br />2. The <strong>CPG</strong>s determine the members of the so called <strong>Dot Product Group</strong> of the job.<br />The <strong>CPG</strong> with the highest cardinality determines the number of <strong>job submissions</strong>.&nbsp; To feed the <strong>job</strong> upon submissions with the proper group of <strong>files</strong>, the encountering of <strong>files</strong> belonging to a <strong>CPG</strong> with <em>less</em> cardinality than the <em>highest</em> one has, will be cyclically repeated.'),('config.input.max','Config_job_port_input_Prametric_Number','In case of <strong>Genuine Input ports</strong> this value determines how much times this <strong>port</strong> will be take part in the <strong>job submissions</strong>. The default value is <strong>1</strong>. For details see the comments at <strong>Parametric Input details</strong>.'),('config.input.hnt','Config_job_port_input_Parametric_ExhaustException','The selectable algorithm defines what to do if the actual <strong>file list</strong> is exhausted i.e. there is no <strong>input file</strong> to the actual file index within the cycle whose length is determined by the value of the <strong>Input numbers</strong>.<br /><br /><em><strong>Values to be selected</strong></em>:<br /><strong>Abort</strong>:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; abort the <strong>job</strong><br /><strong>First</strong>:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; use the <strong>file</strong> identified with index <strong>0</strong><br /><strong>Last</strong>:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; use the <strong>file</strong> identified with the highest index.'),('button.ok','Button_Graph_OK','OK&nbsp;'),('button.delete','Button_Graph_delete','Delete'),('button.abortall','Button_WF_abortall','Suspend all'),('button.cancel','Button_WF_cancel','Cancel'),('button.saveandupload','Button_WF_save_and_upload','Save on Server'),('button.configure','Button_Templ_configure','Configure'),('text.io.100','Label_Copy_to_WN','Copy to WN'),('config.input.remotecopy','Config_job_port_input_remote_copy','This checkbox is applicable in case when the user defines the <strong>remote&nbsp; files</strong> by <strong>Grid File Catalogues</strong>&nbsp; (the file name begins with <strong>lfn:</strong>) <br />If the checkbox <strong>Copy to WN</strong> is <u><strong><em>set</em></strong></u> the system will automatically copy the whole content of the <strong>remote file</strong> to the <strong>Working Node</strong> where the <strong>job</strong> of the user will run, and the new <strong>file</strong> will be put in the working directory of the <strong>WN</strong> as the user has defined it in the Input <strong>port&rsquo;s Internal Filename</strong>. i.e. the user can open the copied <strong>file</strong> traditionally within its <strong>executable</strong>.<br />&nbsp;If the checkbox <strong>Copy to WN</strong> is <u><em><strong>not set</strong></em></u> it is the responsibility of the user to link the remote access api &ndash; for example <strong>GFAL</strong> &ndash; to the <strong>executable</strong> code in order to open and fetch the remote <strong>files</strong> through it. The big advantage of this method is that in one time only a fraction of the whole file must be copied to the Working Node.<br /><u><em><strong>In the current implementation the copy operation is executed even if the checkbox Copy to WN is not set.</strong></em></u><br />'),('button.close','Button_WF_PORT_close','Close'),('buton.quit','Button_WF_PORT_quit','Quit'),('button.quit','Button_WF_PORT_quit_','Quit'),('button.add','Button_WF_PORT_add','Add'),('config.output.intname','Config_job_port_output_interlalfilename','This string value may be referenced in the <strong>executable</strong> of the <strong>Job</strong> in order to <strong>create</strong> and <strong>open</strong> a local<strong> file </strong>assumed to be put in the working directory (or relative to the working directory) of the <strong>host</strong> where the <strong>job</strong> will be <strong>executed</strong>. &nbsp;<br />In the simplest case it will be the name of the created <strong>file</strong> in the destination environment.<br />Certainly it can be a path relative to the working directory of the destination environment as well.<br />The default value of the <strong>Output Port&rsquo;s Internal File Name</strong> associated to the given port of the job is inherited from the &ldquo;<strong>Port Name</strong>&rdquo; of the <strong>Graph</strong> which have been defined in the <strong>Graph Editor</strong> listed under the <u><em><strong>Workflow/Graph</strong></em></u> tab.<br />'),('config.input.waiting','Config_job_port_input_collector','The setting &ldquo;<strong>All</strong>&rdquo; of the radio button <strong>Waiting</strong> defines the &ldquo;<em>Collector</em>&rdquo; property of the associated <strong>port</strong> (and <strong>job</strong>):<br />The <strong>job</strong> will not start until each of the <strong>files</strong> expected to be delivered to this port has arrived.<br />This is the typical case when the user wants to evaluate the results of a <em>Parameter Sweep</em> like calculation.<br />In this case the value defined in the <strong>Input Port&rsquo;s Internal File Name</strong> is just a <em>prefix</em> of the input files to be expected.<br />The postfix _&lt;numb&gt; where &lt;numb&gt; are subsequent integer numbers starting from 0 and will be generated by the system.<br />It is the responsibility of the Job Executable to investigate the runtime environment (for example the working directory) to read and elaborate the<strong> input files</strong> in&nbsp; needed number. <br />The value &ldquo;<strong>One</strong>&rdquo; of <strong>Waiting</strong> is the default setting; for normal case.<br />A <strong>job </strong>may have more than one <strong>input ports</strong> of&nbsp; &ldquo;<em>Collector</em>&rdquo; type.<br />'),('config.output.remotelogical','Config_job_port_output_remote','<p>The &ldquo;<strong>Base</strong>&rdquo; of the destination <strong>URL</strong> of a <strong>remote file</strong>&nbsp; must be defined.<br />The &ldquo;<strong>Base</strong>&rdquo; will be automatically extended with a <em><strong>postfix</strong></em> containing the &ldquo;<strong>_</strong>&rdquo; separator character and a <strong><em>little integer number</em></strong>. <br />The <strong>URL</strong> must have a <em>protocol prefix</em><strong> lfn</strong> or <strong>gsiftp</strong>.<br />The <strong>output file(s) </strong>in both cases will be generated in (or relative to) the <strong>Working Directory</strong> of the local <strong>file system</strong> of the <strong>host</strong> which <strong>executes</strong> the <strong>job. </strong><br />The <strong>output file(s)</strong> will be copied from here to the <em>destination</em> depending on the kind of the <strong>URL</strong>.<br /><br />1. <em>Simple file case</em> &ndash; not a <strong>Parameter Sweep port</strong>:<br />The integer number mentioned in the <strong><em>postfix</em></strong> of the <strong>URL</strong> is <strong>0 </strong><br />1.1 <em>prefix</em> <strong>lfn</strong>:<br />The <em>prefix</em> <strong>lfn</strong>: will be used in case of &ldquo;high&rdquo; level <strong>remote file</strong> definition, when the<strong> URL</strong> refers to a logical name according to the convention of the <strong>LFC Grid File Catalogue</strong>. The corresponding&nbsp; ENVIRONMENT variables&nbsp; are set by the system for each <strong>Virtual Organizations</strong> supporting the <strong>LFC </strong>catalogues.<br />At the moment this setting is being done in script files handled by the <strong>System Administrator</strong>.<br />The destination of the <strong>file(s)</strong> is a <strong>Storage Element.</strong><br /><br />&nbsp;<br />1.2 <em>prefix</em> <strong>gsiftp</strong>:<br />The <em>prefix</em> <strong>gsiftp</strong>: will be used if the <strong>remote file</strong> is implemented as a shared <strong>file</strong> stored in the local file system of a<strong> remote host</strong>&nbsp; accessible by a <strong>GT2</strong> infrastructure. <br /><br />&nbsp;2 . Multiple file case&nbsp; -<strong> Parameter Sweep (PS) port</strong>:<br />The <strong><em>integer number</em></strong> mentioned in the <strong><em>postfix</em></strong> of the <strong>URL</strong> corresponds to the actual sequence number of the recently generated <strong>file</strong>, where the first generation has the index <strong>0</strong>.<br />The <strong>output port </strong>becomes a<strong> PS port</strong> if any of the predecessor of the <strong>job</strong> (or the<strong> job</strong> itself) generates multiple files conducted to this <strong>port</strong>. This can happen by any (or by the combination) of the following cases:<br />- Any of the mentioned <strong>jobs</strong> has a <strong>PS input port</strong> fed by more than <strong>1</strong> <strong>input file</strong><br />- Any of the&nbsp; <strong>output ports</strong> of the mentioned <strong>jobs</strong> playing a role in the call of the current <strong>job</strong> as a <strong>Generator port</strong> producing more than <strong>1 files</strong><br />- The current <strong>port</strong> is a <strong>Generator port</strong> producing more than 1 file. </p>'),('config.output.remotehost','Config_job_port_output_StorageElement','A <strong>Storage Element (SE)</strong> must be defined in the case when the <strong>remote file</strong> generation is defined by <strong>Logical File Catalogue (LFC)</strong> names.<br />In this case the <strong>file URLs</strong> are prefixed with the name of the protocol: <strong>lfn</strong>.<br />Depending on the <strong>grids</strong> the <strong>SE</strong> candidates can be found in the descriptors of <strong>sites</strong> which are accessible from the <u><em><strong>Information System/LCGMonitor<br /></strong></em></u> tab.'),('config.output.type','Config_job_port_output_storagetype','This setting has meaning only if the <strong>output file</strong> is not a <strong>remote</strong> file, i.e. the field &ldquo;<strong>Base of Output Port&rsquo;s Remote File Name</strong>&rdquo; is empty.<br />1.<br />The value <em><strong>Permanent</strong></em> means that the file which will be created on the <strong>Working Node</strong> as a consequence of the job&rsquo;s run must be preserved even after the termination of the whole <strong>workflow</strong>.<br />With other words <strong>permanent files</strong> are parts of the <strong>result set of the workflow instance</strong> and can be downloaded to the user&rsquo;s computer after the termination of the <strong>job</strong>/<strong>workflow</strong>.<br />The user can download&nbsp; these values either by the proper <strong>get&hellip;</strong> commands of the <u><em><strong>Workflow/Storage</strong></em></u> tab or by accessing jobs with the Details button on the <u><em><strong>Workflow/Concrete</strong></em></u> tab.<br />2.<br />The value <em><strong>Volatile</strong></em> means that the value will not be used after the generated <strong>file</strong> has been successfully consumed by the following <strong>job</strong>(s). These <strong>jobs</strong> are the <strong>destinations</strong> of the <strong>channel</strong>s whose shared <strong>output port</strong> is the current one. <br />'),('button.outputs','Button_Download_outputs','get Outputs'),('button.instance','Button_Download_instance','get Instance'),('button.all','Button_Download_all','get All'),('button.allwithoutlogs','Button_Download_all_without_logs','get All but Logs'),('button.inputs','Button_Download_Inputs','get Inputs'),('config.output.maincount','Config_job_port_output_Generator','If the value <strong>yes</strong> will be selected on the <strong>Generator</strong> radio button, then it means that the <strong>job</strong> will be a <strong>Generator</strong>.<br /><strong>Generator</strong> is a <strong>job</strong> which produces more than 1 <strong>files</strong> during a single <strong>job execution</strong> on a single <strong>port</strong>.<br />It is assumed that the <strong>job executable</strong> produces proper number of <strong>output files</strong> with the following name convention: the <strong>files</strong> generated in (or relative to) the <strong>working directory</strong> of the <strong>working node</strong> have the <em><strong>prefix</strong></em> defined in <strong>Output Port&rsquo;s Internal File Name</strong> extended with a <em><strong>postfix</strong></em> containing the separator character &ldquo;<strong>_</strong>&rdquo; and a <em><strong>little integer number</strong></em> starting from 0.<br />However the number of files generated by the executable may be different from the <strong>Generator</strong> number <strong>X</strong> defined here.<br />In every case the number <strong>X</strong> defines the number of calls of the later <strong>jobs</strong>.<br />If the number of generated <strong>output files</strong> exceeds number <strong>X</strong>, the files with the high induces will not be used.<br />In the case when the number of generated <strong>files</strong> is less than <strong>X</strong> run time error will be reported.&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;'),('button.upload','Button_Upload_Object','Upload'),('button.load','Button_Import_Show_List','Refresh/show list'),('button.execute','Button_Import_Execute','Execute'),('portal.config.templatelist','Config_WF_changeTemplate','At the moment this is an unsupported operation!'),('button.set','Button_Remoting_Add to List','add to List'),('button.viewkey','Button_Remoting_view_key','view key'),('button.wievkey','Button_Rremoting_wiev_Key','view key'),('button.suspend','Button_WF_suspend','Suspend'),('button.resume','Button_WF_resume','Resume'),('error.executejob.jobmanager','Java_job_missing_jobmanager','Missing type of jobmanager'),('text.configure.workflowname','Selected_WF_name','Workflow name:'),('button.shortdetails','Button_WF_show_details','Details'),('button.logg','Button_WW_show_Logbook','Logbook'),('button.stdout','Button_WF_show_stdout','std. Output'),('button.stderr','Button_WF_show_stderr','std. Error'),('button.stdoutput','Button_WF_show_output','Download file output'),('button.outtput','Button_WF_show_output2','Download file output'),('button.output','Button_WF_show_output3','Download file output'),('config.job.iworkflow','Config_job_embedded_selector','The list box opens a selectable list of <strong>Workflows</strong> constrained by a <strong>Template</strong>.<br />The selected <strong>Workflow</strong> will be embedded in this <strong>Job</strong>.<br />In an eventual later configuration phase selected by the <u><em><strong>Job Inputs and Outputs</strong></em></u> tab the entries<br />&rdquo;<strong>In embedded Workflow</strong>&rdquo; will enumerate the <strong>Ports</strong> of the <strong>embedded Workflow</strong> which may be associated with the&nbsp; <strong>Ports</strong> of the caller (or envelop) <strong>Job</strong>.<br />'),('config.job.servicetype','Config_job_service_type','Selector of <em>communication protocol</em>s for Web Service Servers.<br />Currently only <strong>Soap</strong> may be chosen with <strong>Apache Axis</strong> implementation. <br />'),('config.job.serviceurl','Config_job_service_URL','Selectable list of remote <strong>hosts</strong> offering <em>Web Services</em> corresponding to communication protocol defined in the <strong>select Type</strong>. <br />Currently the list is generated by the Administrator of the gUSE.'),('config.job.servicemethod','Config_job_service_methode','Selectable list of functions offered by&nbsp; the <em>Web Service</em> defined by <strong>select Service</strong>.'),('portal.wfdemo.execute','Demo_download','The selected demonstration&nbsp; object ( <strong>Graph</strong>, <strong>Template</strong> or <strong>Concrete Workflow</strong>) will be transferred in the namespace of the <strong>user</strong>. <br />It works similar to <strong>Import</strong>. <br />The main difference is, that there is no <strong>Export</strong> to this collection, so only the <strong>Administrator</strong> can add objects to the list.<br />To avoid the collisions of names the corresponding <strong>name</strong>(s) can be altered before the transfer.'),('portal.wfdemo.graf','Demo_graph_change_comment','By setting the checkbox the user indicates the intention to rename the <strong>graph</strong> part of the object to be imported.'),('portal.wfdemo.abst','Demo_template_change_comment','By setting the checkbox the user indicates the intention to rename the <strong>template</strong> part of the object to be imported.'),('portal.wfdemo.real','Demo_workflow_change_comment','By setting the checkbox the user indicates the intention to rename the <strong>workflow </strong>part of the object to be imported.'),('portal.WorkflowData.status.15','WF_status_Suspended','Aborted'),('portal.WorkflowDataStatus.22','WF_status_SusupendedReal','Suspending'),('button.send','export_confirm','Export'),('help.minta','MINTAHELP','<p>\r\ndsd<sub>sd</sub><font color=\"#ffff00\"><sub>as</sub>d<sup>as&thorn;</sup>s</font>ss \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nrefdfgds<img src=\"../portal30/admin/Image/lamp.jpg\" alt=\"lamp.jpg\" title=\"lamp.jpg\" width=\"39\" height=\"33\" /> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nrztzaaaaaaaaaaasssssssssssssddddddddddddddd\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\ntr<img src=\"../portal30/tinymce/jscripts/tiny_mce/plugins/emotions/images/smiley-innocent.gif\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Innocent\" title=\"Innocent\" />  \r\n</p>'),('button.submitall','Button_Submit_All','Submit All'),('button.info','Button_Info','Info'),('button.details','Button_Details','Details'),('button.submit','Button_Submit','Submit'),('button.back','Button_Back','Back'),('button.refreshinstances','Button_Refresh_Instances','Refresh'),('button.visualize','Button_Visualize','Visualize'),('button.modifygraf','Button_Modify_Graph','Modify Graph'),('button.modifytemplate','Button_Modify_Template','Modify Template'),('text.wfdemo.download','Button_Demo_Import','Import'),('text.wfimport.import','WF_Import_import','Import'),('text.wfimport.delete','WF_Import_delete','Delete'),('text.wfimport.application','WF_Import_application','Application'),('text.wfimport.project','WF_Import_project','Project'),('text.wfimport.concrete','WF_Import_concrete','Concrete'),('text.wfimport.template','WF_Import_template','Template'),('text.wfimport.graph','WF_Import_graph','Graph'),('text.wfimport.wflistfromrepo','WF_Import_listheader_post','list of selectables'),('text.wfimport.wflistisempty','WF_Import_list_is_empty','list is empty'),('text.io.50','Port_Connect_to_embedded','Connect input port to a Job/Input port of the embedded WF'),('text.ctemplate.newtempname','Config_Template_TemplateName','Template name:'),('text.ctemplate.parentname','Config_Template_Base_WF','Base Workflow name:'),('text.ctemplate.close','Config_Template_close','Close'),('text.ctemplate.free','Config_Template_free','Free'),('button.create','Config_Template_Button_save_created','Save'),('text.ctemplate.check','Config_Template_Conf_Header','<strong>Settings of the subsequent job with the name:<br /> </strong>'),('text.ctemplate.input','Config_Template_Inp_Port_Header','<em>Settings of the input port named as:</em>'),('text.ctemplate.output','Config_Template_Out_Port_Header','<em>Settings of the output port named as:</em>'),('text.ctemplate.key.binary','Config_Template_key_binary','<strong>Executable code of binary<br /> </strong>'),('text.ctemplate.key.gridtype','Config_Template_key_gridtype','<strong>Type </strong>of submitter<strong><br /> </strong>'),('text.ctemplate.key.jobmanager','Config_Template_key_jobmanager','<strong>Job Manager<br /> </strong>'),('text.ctemplate.key.jobistype','Config_Template_key_jobistype','<strong>Job is <br /> </strong>'),('text.ctemplate.key.type','Config_Template_key_type','<strong>Kind of binary<br /> </strong>'),('text.ctemplate.key.resource','Config_Template_key_resource','<strong>Resource/Broker<br /> </strong>'),('text.ctemplate.key.grid','Config_Template_key_grid','<strong>Grid<br /> </strong>'),('text.ctemplate.key.intname','Config_Template_key_intname','<strong>Internal File Name<br /> </strong>'),('text.ctemplate.key.pequalvalue','Config_Template_key_pequalvalue','Port dependent condition<strong> value<br /> </strong>'),('text.ctemplate.key.pequaltype','Config_Template_key_pequaltype','Port dependent condition<strong> type<br /> </strong>'),('text.ctemplate.key.dpid','Config_Template_key_dpid','<strong>Dot and Cross PID<br /> </strong>'),('text.ctemplate.key.max','Config_Template_key_max','Parameter Sweep<strong> Input Numbers<br /> </strong>'),('text.ctemplate.key.pequalinput','Config_Template_key_pequalinput','Port dependent condition<strong> File </strong>on Port<strong>  </strong>'),('text.ctemplate.key.remote','Config_Template_key_remote','Recently defined External File is<strong> Remote<br /> </strong>'),('text.ctemplate.key.hnt','Config_Template_key_hnt','code of <strong>Exception at exhausted Input  </strong>'),('text.ctemplate.key.file','Config_Template_key_file','Recently defined Input File name to <strong>Upload  </strong>'),('text.ctemplate.key.maincount','Confiig_Template_key_naincount','<strong>Generator, if the value of the input field is bigger than 1</strong><strong>  </strong>'),('text.ctemplate.key.waiting','Config_Template_key_waiting','<strong>Waiting</strong> flag<strong>  </strong>'),('help._gwkflist_WAR_portal30_','HelpTextTab_Graph','<p>This tab serves the management of workflow <strong>Graphs</strong>.<br />Graphs are created and modified with the <strong>Graph Editor</strong>.<br />The Graph Editor runs on the users desktop in a separate window dedicated to the given <strong>Graph</strong> object.<br />The Graph Editor can be called either by clicking on the <strong><em>Graph Editor</em></strong> button &ndash; for example to create a new <strong>Graph</strong>, or by clicking on the <em><strong>Edit</strong></em> button for example in the case when the user wants to modify, or copy an existing <strong>Graph</strong>.</p><p>An existing Graph can be downloaded to the user&rsquo;s computer by hitting the <strong><em>Download</em></strong> button. <br />A later upload can be done in the <strong>Workflow/Upload</strong> tab. The user may select there to change the name of the <strong>Graph</strong> to be uploaded as the <strong>Graph</strong> objects of a user have a shared namespace (with the exception of Graphs of the embedded workflows within <strong>Projects</strong> and <strong>Applications</strong>), and the name collision is detected and prohibited.</p><p>Clicking the <strong><em>Delete</em></strong> button the user deletes the <strong>Graph</strong> object from the graph list.</p><p>Clicking the <strong><em>Export</em></strong> button the user uploads the Graph object in a <strong>Repository</strong> shared among all Users. <br />A later reload from the Repository can be done on the <strong>Workflow/Upload</strong> tab</p><p>The <strong><em>Refresh</em></strong> button serves the synchronization: All existing <strong>Graph</strong> objects (whose list&nbsp;will be extended by the <strong>save</strong>d&nbsp;products of the Graph Editors running parallel on the user&rsquo;s computer) will be listed.</p>'),('help._gwkflist_WAR_portal30_','HelpTextTab_Graph','<p>This tab serves the management of workflow <strong>Graphs</strong>.<br /><strong>Graphs</strong> are created and modified by the <strong>Graph Editor</strong>.<br /><br />The <strong>Graph Editor</strong> runs on the user&rsquo;s desktop in a separate window dedicated to the given <strong>Graph</strong> object.<br /><br />The <strong>Graph Editor</strong> can be called either by clicking on the <em><strong>Graph Editor</strong></em> button &ndash; for example to create a new <strong>Graph</strong>, or by clicking&nbsp; on the <strong><em>Edit</em></strong> button for example in the case when the user wants to modify, or copy an existing <strong>Graph</strong>.</p><p>An existing <strong>Graph</strong> can be downloaded to the user&rsquo;s computer by hitting the <strong><em>Download</em></strong> button. A later upload can be done in the <strong>Workflow/Upload</strong> tab. The user may select there to change the name of the <strong>Graph</strong> to be uploaded as the <strong>Graph</strong> objects of a user have a shared namespace (with the exception of Graphs of the <strong>embedded workflows</strong> within <strong>Projects</strong> and <strong>Applications</strong>), and the name collision is detected and prohibited.</p><p>Clicking the <em><strong>Delete</strong></em> button the user deletes the <strong>Graph</strong> object from the graph list.</p><p>Clicking the <strong><em>Export</em></strong> button the user uploads the <strong>Graph</strong> object in a <strong>Repository</strong> shared among all users. A later reload from the <strong>Repository</strong> can be done on the <strong>Workflow/Upload</strong> tab </p><p>The <strong><em>Refresh</em></strong> button serves the synchronization: All existing <strong>Graph</strong> objects (whose list will be extended by the saved products of the <strong>Graph Editors</strong> running parallel on the user&rsquo;s computer) will be listed.</p>'),('portal.graph.exportdesc','HelpTextTab_GraphExport','The user can publish as <strong>Export Notes</strong> the detailed description of the <strong>Graph</strong> to be exported for the whole user community accessing the <strong>Repository</strong>.<br />The text will belong to the given <strong>Graph</strong> and will be readable in the <strong>Workflow/Import</strong> tab in the <strong>Notes</strong> column.'),('help._newwkf_WAR_portal30_','HelpTextTab_NewWorkflow','<p>A new <strong>Workflow</strong> can be defined on this <strong>tab</strong>. A <strong>Workflow </strong>explicitly or implicitly must reference a <strong>Graph</strong>. The user selects the root of the workflow generation with the <strong>radio button</strong> <strong><em>Create from</em></strong>.<br />Depending on the choice, an existing <strong>Graph</strong> or an existing <strong>Template</strong> (referencing already a <strong>Graph</strong>) or an existing <strong>different Workflow</strong> (also referencing a <strong>Graph</strong>) can be used to create a new <strong>Workflow</strong> with a user defined <em><strong>name</strong></em> and with a user defined <strong><em>Optional note</em></strong>.<br /><br />The <strong>configuration</strong> of the created <strong>Workflow</strong> can be performed in the <strong>tab Workflow/Concrete</strong> by clicking the <strong><em>Configure</em></strong> button in the line belonging to the created <strong>Workflow</strong>.</p><p>By giving the <strong>Name for the new workflow</strong> please note that the <strong>Workflows</strong> and <strong>Templates</strong> have a shared namespace and all entries must be called differently.</p><p><strong><em>OK</em></strong> button closes and confirms the creation.</p><p>The <strong><em>Refresh</em></strong> button serves the synchronization: All existing <strong>Graph</strong> objects (whose list will be extended by the saved products of the <strong>Graph Editors</strong> running parallel on the user&rsquo;s computer) will be listed in the checklist belonging to the <strong>Graph</strong> selector.</p>'),('help.realworkflowlist','HelpTextTab_WorkflowList','<p>This tab lists the configurable and submitable <strong>workflows</strong> owned by the current user.<br />Workflows listed here are either have been created using the <strong>Workflow/Create</strong> tab or have been uploaded from the user&rsquo;s computer using the <strong>Workflow/Upload</strong> tab or have been imported from the central <strong>Repository</strong> using the <strong>Workflow/Import</strong> tab.</p><p><br />Users can decide whether these workflows are either fully configured or their semantics can be defined or altered.<br /><br />I.<br />In case of fully configured workflows the user can submit them if he/she has a valid proxy certificate (can be uploaded on the <strong>Certificates/Download</strong> tab) to all the <strong>Grid resources</strong> requested by the <strong>workflow</strong>. </p><p>The user can control the fully qualified and submitable state of the <strong>workflow</strong> with the <strong><em>Info</em></strong> button by listing the undefined features/settings of the given <strong>workflow</strong>. At the moment this test does not include the eventual problems of the <strong>embedded Workflows</strong> as these objects will be activated only in runtime.</p><p><br />A correct workflow can be submitted by using the <strong><em>Submit</em></strong> button.<br />Upon submission a new object, the <strong>Workflow Instance</strong> will be created. <br />The <strong>Workflow Instance</strong> contains additional information (state of the Workflow Instance and among others the created log and output files ).<br />During the obligatory submission conforming process the user may add a comment in order to distinguish the different <strong>Workflow Instances</strong> which have been created manually. This is called <em>direct submission</em>.</p><p><em>Indirect submission</em> occurs if a given <strong>workflow</strong> has been mentioned in a <strong>job configuration</strong> to interpret the semantics of that job.(<strong>Embedded Workflow</strong>). During the execution of the <strong>workflow</strong> containing the mentioned<strong> job</strong> the following happens: Upon the elaboration of that <strong>job</strong>, the workflow interpreter executes this &ldquo;call&rdquo; as a new workflow submission with the consequence that a new <strong>Workflow Instance</strong> will be created from the <strong>embedded workflow</strong>. However in this case an automatically created unique label will distinguish this <strong>Workflow Instance</strong> from the others.<br />The instances of the embedded workflows can be reached as if they would be the instances of shared workflows. It follows that the workflows used for embedding must be also defined (fully qualified) and presented on this workflow list.</p><p>The <strong><em>Details</em> button</strong> opens a window where all the existing <strong>Instances</strong> of the <strong>Workflow</strong> are enumerated and ready for more detailed analysis and manipulations.</p><p>On the associated state statistics table the total number of the <strong>instances</strong> of a given <strong>workflow</strong> are subdivided into four categories according to their run time states:<br /><strong><em>Submitted - Running - Finished - Error</em></strong>.<br />&nbsp;<br />With the <strong><em>Suspend</em> button</strong> all <strong>instances</strong> of a given <strong>workflow</strong> can be suspended. (Suspended <strong>workflow instances</strong> can be <strong>resumed</strong> individually in a sub window which may be opened with the <strong><em>Details</em> button</strong>.)</p><p>A <strong>workflow</strong> can be deleted with all of its <strong>instances</strong> by using the <strong><em>Delete</em> button</strong>.</p><p>A <strong>workflow</strong> can be exported to the <strong>Repository</strong> by using the <strong><em>Export</em> button</strong>. </p><p>II.<br /><br />The <strong><em>Configure</em> button</strong> opens the root of the workflow configuration window, where the graph of the workflow appears. Clicking on a <strong>job</strong> or on a <strong>port</strong> icon belonging to a <strong>job</strong>, the given item can be defined/modified. </p>'),('help.wrkinst','HelpTextTab_WorkflowInstance','<p>On this window the existing <strong>Instances</strong> of the selected <strong>Workflow</strong> are listed. They are ready for more detailed analysis and can be manipulated. </p><p>The analysis can be done on a four level hierarchy where the encountering of the <strong>Instances</strong> is the root level. (Level 1)<br />&nbsp;<br />From here the user can select to inspect the list of <strong>Jobs</strong> belonging to the selected <strong>workflow instance</strong> (Level 2, can be reached with the <strong><em>Details</em></strong> button).<br />&nbsp;<br />A single <strong>Job</strong> may have several <strong>Instances</strong> (and proper discriminating induces in their names) due to the fact, that the <strong>job</strong> may run several times within the control of a given <strong>workflow instance</strong> (if parameter sweep had been defined earlier) creating a new <strong>Job Instance</strong> each time (Level 3, reachable by the <strong><em>View Content(s)</em></strong> button).<br /><br />Stepping even deeper into the hierarchy, the <strong>log</strong> and <strong>output files</strong> of a <strong>job instance</strong> can be reached (listed or downloaded) (Level 4, by using the following <strong>buttons</strong>:</p><strong><ul><li><strong><em>Logbook</em></strong>, </li><li><strong><em>std. Output</em></strong>, </li><li><strong><em>std. Error</em></strong>, </li><li><strong><em>Download file output</em></strong>).</li></ul></strong><p>On the <strong>workflow instance</strong> level (Level 1) the user can </p><ul><li>suspend/resume<strong> the Workflow Instance</strong> by the toggle of the <strong><em>Suspend</em>/<em>Resume</em></strong> buttons,</li><li>delete the <strong>workflow instance</strong> object with the <strong><em>Delete</em></strong> button or </li><li>investigate it graphically in a timeline diagram opened by the <strong><em>Visualize</em></strong> button. <br /></li></ul>'),('help.configure','HelpTextTab_WorkflowConfiguration','<p>I.<br />This is the main window of the <strong>Workflow</strong> configuration.</p><p>The goal is to define - in a singe or in several sessions &ndash; all the necessary attributes which should be associated&nbsp;&nbsp; to the <strong>Jobs</strong> (empty at start) defined by the <strong>Workflow Graph</strong> in order to create a fully defined, executable&nbsp; <strong>Workflow</strong> with given semantics.</p><p>II.<br />The <strong>Workflow Graph</strong>&nbsp;has been&nbsp;assigned to the <strong>Workflow </strong>in the <strong>Workflow/Create Concrete</strong> tab. <br /><br />However it is possible on this page to substitute the original <strong>Graph</strong> with a new one. The reason behind this option is the possibility of the situation when the user wants modify the graph of the tested and configured <strong>workflow</strong> and does not want to repeat the whole - sometimes tedious and error prone - configuration process.<br />If the new <strong>Graph</strong> is a modification of the old one and common parts can be found, the system tries to identify them and to copy the inherited configuration into the proper <strong>Jobs</strong> of the new <strong>Graph</strong>.&nbsp; <br />The new modified&nbsp;<strong> Graph</strong> can be selected from the <strong>list box</strong>.&nbsp; For the confirmation of the process press the <strong><em>Modify Graph</em></strong> button. </p><p>The same applies if there is a Workflow Template which indirectly defines a Graph. <br /><em>At the moment the changing of the template &ldquo;under&rdquo; an existing workflow is not supported.</em></p><p>III.<br />The actual configuration must be done individually for each <strong>Job</strong>. Either a <strong>Job</strong> or a <strong>Port</strong> belonging to a <strong>Job</strong> can be selected by clicking on its icon: A proper form will be opened, which must be filled and closed.</p><p>IV.<br />Please note, that the configuration happens only within the browser and the modifications will not be saved on the server until you close it by clicking&nbsp; on the <strong><em>Save on Server</em></strong> button. </p><p>Before doing&nbsp;that the user may decide to erase all existing <strong>Workflow Instances</strong> belonging to the given workflow by selecting the <strong><em>Delete old instances</em></strong> radio button.</p>'),('help.job','HelpTextTab_JobConfiguration','<p>I.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Introduction&nbsp;</strong></p><p>This is the main window of the job configuration.</p><p>It contains four selectable sub tabs where the actually selected is colored to red:</p><ul><li><strong>Job Executable</strong></li><li><strong>Job Inputs and Outputs</strong></li><li><strong>JDL-RSL</strong></li><li><strong>Job Configuration History</strong></li></ul><p>The active one by default is the <strong>Job Executable</strong> and it has distinguished importance and its setting determines whether the tabs <strong>Job Inputs and Outputs</strong> and <strong>JDL-RSL</strong> have a meaning at all.</p><p><strong>Job Executable</strong> determines:</p><ul><li>the basic type of algorithm (<strong>embedded workflow</strong> invocation, <strong>service call</strong>, <strong>binary code</strong>);</li><li>the way the algorithm is associated to an executing resource (in case of <strong>binary code</strong>);&nbsp;</li><li>the algorithm itself.</li></ul><p>There may be a difference whether the algorithm is supplied by the user in the form of an uploaded code file or it is only selectable from a list offered online by a remote <strong>resource</strong> (when the base algorithm is a <strong>service call</strong> or when the <strong>Type</strong> of the resource is <strong>gemlca</strong>)<br /><br />In both cases control parameters can be associated to the algorithm.<br /><br />The fields of the form in case of a <strong>binary code</strong> are grouped in the following categories:<br /><strong>Type</strong>, <strong>Grid</strong>, <strong>Resource/Broker</strong>, <strong>JobManager</strong> determines the destination where the job will be executed.<br /><br />The fields <strong>Kind of binary</strong>, <strong>MPI Node Number</strong>, <strong>Executable code of binary</strong>, <strong>Parameter</strong> define the code of the algorithm to be uploaded.<br /><br />These settings must be confirmed by clicking on the <em><strong>Save</strong></em> button. </p><p>Please remember that saving the job does not ensures the saving/updating of the workflow in itself:<br />The user must hit the <em><strong>Save on Server</strong></em> button in the &quot;parent window&quot; before leaving the workflow configuration.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>II.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Special considerations of Workflow embedding</strong>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">The insulated computational logic hidden behind a single job may be the invocation of an existing defined <strong>workflow</strong> of the same user. As the <strong>input ports</strong> of the <strong>caller</strong> <strong>jobs</strong> may be associated to certain genuine input ports of the <strong>called</strong> (<em><strong>embedded</strong></em>) <strong>workflow</strong> and certain <strong>output ports</strong> of the <strong>called</strong> (<em><strong>embedded</strong></em>) <strong>workflow</strong> can be associated to the <strong>output ports</strong> of the <strong>caller job</strong>, the mode of evaluation corresponds to the classical subroutine call paradigm. <br /> Moreover the <strong>call</strong> can be - explicitly, or implicitly - a recursive one as a new <strong>Workflow Instance</strong> object will be created upon the submission of a <strong>workflow</strong> (storing the intermediate files encoding the run time state and the output files of the workflow).<br /> <br /> With the common application of the input condition (on job ports) and with the application of the recursive embedding the DAG imposed ban on the repeated call of a job of the workflow can be circumvented.<br /> The other trivial way of bypassing is the PS. </p>  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>  <p class=\"MsoNormal\"> <em><strong>However in the current implementation there are rather strong restrictions when the embedded workflow call can be used:</strong></em><br /> <!--[if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br /> <!--[endif]--></p>  <ul><li>An <strong>embedded workflow</strong>, within a <strong>PS environment</strong> - knowing nothing about the number of its proposed invocation - can not be used. The main cause is that the index space of the PS is calculated &ndash; at the moment &ndash; in a static way, before the invocation of the workflow.</li><li> On the <strong>input</strong> side only the passing of the <strong>local</strong> (uploaded or channel) <strong>files</strong> are supported, but there is <strong>no support</strong> for <strong>remote files</strong>, or for unnamed files built of <strong>direct values</strong> which may be defined during the <strong>port</strong> configuration at common <strong>input ports</strong>.</li><li> Neither can be used the <strong>SQL input </strong>&ndash; which would combine the difficulties mentioned at the <strong>PS</strong> and the <strong>direct value</strong> cases.</li><li> On the <strong>output side</strong> the <strong>local file</strong> generated by the embedded workflow can not be associated to a <strong>remote file</strong> defined on the <strong>output port</strong> of the <strong>caller job</strong>. </li><li>Neither the <strong>ports</strong> of the <strong>embedded workflow</strong> associated to a <strong>remote file</strong> may not be involved in parameter passing. <span>&nbsp;</span></li></ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\">     <!--[if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--> <!--[endif]--></p>  <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>Technically the configuration of embedded workflow call happens in two steps</strong></p>  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">1.<span>&nbsp; </span>In the <strong><em>Job Executable</em></strong> tab, ( <strong><em>Workflow/Concrete</em></strong> tab -&gt; selected <strong>WF</strong> -&gt; selected <strong>Job</strong> )<span>&nbsp; </span>the choice &ldquo;<strong>Interpretation of job as Workflow</strong>&rdquo; will be selected as <strong>Job execution model</strong>, and from the list labeled as &ldquo;<strong>for embedding select a workflow created from a Template</strong>&rdquo; a proper <strong>workflow</strong> will be selected.<br /> 2. In the parallel<strong></strong> <em><strong>Job Inputs and Outputs</strong>tab</em> there is the option &ldquo;<strong>Connect input port to a Job/Input port of the embedded WF </strong>&rdquo; <span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>to each input port of the caller <strong>job</strong>. If the option is selected then the list of associable <strong>input ports</strong> of the <strong>embedded workflow</strong> will be selectable and showed as a <strong>Job</strong>/<strong>Port Name</strong> pair.<br /> <br /> Similar is true for the <strong>output ports</strong> selecting the option &ldquo;<strong>Connect output port to a Job/Output port of the embedded WF</strong>&rdquo; </p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>'),('help.io','HelpTextTab_JobIoConfiguration','<p>This form lists the <strong>Ports</strong> belonging to the actual <strong>Job</strong> with the current configuration possibilities.<br /><br />Please remember to select a <strong>port</strong> to be configured. <br /><br />The <strong>ports</strong> subdivided into two lists: <br />First the <strong>input ports</strong>, after the <strong>output ports</strong> are encountered. Blue horizontal bars separate the individual port settings.<br /><br />Each <strong>port</strong> inherits the <strong>Port Name</strong> from the <strong>Graph</strong> description as the default value for the <strong>Internal File Name</strong>. As the uploaded <strong>executable code</strong> references the proper <strong>Internal File Name</strong> in order to open an <strong>input</strong> or an <strong>output file</strong>, its value must be known &ndash; and set - by the user to configure the connection properly. &nbsp;<br /><br />In several other respects the configuration of <strong>input </strong>and <strong>output ports</strong> may be different.<br /><br />In case of <strong>input ports</strong>:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>There is a possibility to define a <strong>condition</strong> about the content of the <strong>file</strong> in order to permit/refuse the execution of the associated<strong> job</strong>.</li><li>There is a wide palette (<strong>Upload</strong>, <strong>Remote</strong>, <strong>Value</strong>, <strong>SQL</strong>) to define the external source / content of the values to be forwarded through the given <strong>input port.<br /></strong>Note, that&nbsp; the <strong>port </strong>in this case must not be the endpoint of a <strong>channel</strong> (statically associated to the <strong>output port</strong> of a<strong> job</strong> of the same <strong>workflow</strong> by the <strong>Graph</strong> description) <strong><br /></strong></li><li>There is an option (<strong>Parametric Input Details</strong>) to define a multiplication factor for<strong> job</strong> submissions and to relate the input sets forwarded through this <strong>port</strong> to other sibling <strong>ports</strong> of the same <strong>job</strong>.</li></ul><p><br />In case of <strong>output ports</strong>:</p><ul><li>There is an optional field to define the destination if the respective output stream of the <strong>job</strong> is directed to a <strong>remote file</strong>.</li><li>By default the <strong>Generator</strong> value is set to 1 which can be modified in case of a <strong>Parameter Sweep</strong> workflow, when the <strong>job</strong> is instructed to produce the required number of <strong>output files</strong> through this <strong>port</strong> in order to trigger the proper number of invocations of the following connected <strong>jobs</strong>.</li></ul><p><br />A special optional field appears for each <strong>port</strong> if the user has defined the current job to call an <strong>embedded workflow</strong> in the <strong><em>Job Executable</em></strong> tab i.e. the <strong>radio button</strong> value <strong>Interpretation of the job as a Workflow</strong> has been selected.<br />This entry field is labeled as &ldquo;<strong>Connect to embedded WF&rsquo;s port</strong>&rdquo; posing the current <strong>port</strong> as &quot;formal parameter&quot; to which&nbsp; the proper <strong>port</strong> of the called (<strong>embedded</strong>) <strong>Workflow</strong> as &quot;actual parameter&quot; can be associated. <br />The association ensures the automatic <strong>file</strong> transfers before /after the execution of the <strong>embedded workflow</strong> respectively. <br />Please note that the association is not obligatory in the <strong>input port</strong> case: There may be a defined <strong>input value</strong> which have been associated to the proper <strong>port</strong> of the <strong>embedded workflow</strong>.<br /><br />These settings must be confirmed by clicking on the <strong><em>OK</em></strong> button.<br /><br />Please remember that saving the <strong>port</strong> settings of the <strong>job</strong> does not ensure the saving/updating of the <strong>workflow</strong> itself:<br />The user must hit the <strong>Save on Server</strong> button in the &quot;parent window&quot;&nbsp; before leaving the <strong>workflow</strong> configuration.&nbsp;<br /> </p>'),('config.input.embed','Config_job_port_input_embed','Select <strong>Yes</strong> if you want to connect this <strong>port</strong> to a selectable input port of the defined <strong>embedded Workflow</strong>'),('config.input.iinput','Config_job_port_input_assocEbeddedPort','<p>Select<strong> </strong>the proper <strong>input</strong> <strong>port</strong> of the <strong>embedded Workflow</strong> to be associated with the actual <strong>input port</strong>. </p><p>To help the user to identify the proper<strong> port</strong>, the list of possible ports is encountered by&nbsp; hierarchical names:&nbsp; concatenating relating <strong>Job</strong> and <strong>Port&nbsp;  names</strong> separated by &quot;/&quot;.</p>'),('text.io.51','Port_Connect_to_ebedded_output','Connect output port to a Job/Output port of the embedded WF'),('config.output.embedparam','Config_job_port_output_embedd_Enab','Select <strong>Yes</strong> if you want to connect this <strong>port</strong> to a subseqently selectable output port of the defined <strong>embedded Workflow <br /></strong>'),('config.output.ioutput','Config_job_port_output_assocEbeddedPort','<p>Select<strong> </strong>the proper <strong>output</strong> <strong>port</strong> of the <strong>embedded Workflow</strong> to be associated with the actual <strong>output port</strong>. </p><p>To help the user to identify the proper<strong> port</strong>, the list of possible ports is encountered by&nbsp; hierarchical names:&nbsp; concatenating relating <strong>Job</strong> and <strong>Port&nbsp;  names</strong> separated by &quot;/&quot;. </p>'),('help.description','HelpTextTab_JobJdlRsl','<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana\">On this form <strong>Grid</strong> and <strong>middleware</strong> specific additional information can be defined. <br />Traditionally this information is stored in a file edited by the user, meeting the specifications of the proper <em><strong>job descriptor languages</strong></em> like <strong>JDL</strong>,&nbsp; <strong>RSL</strong>,&nbsp; etc.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana\">The <strong>gUSE</strong> generates these <strong>Job</strong> descriptors automatically extended with the <strong>entries</strong> the user has defined explicitly on this form.<br />&nbsp;<br />These <strong>entries</strong> consist of <strong>key -</strong>&nbsp;<strong>value</strong> pairs, where the set of selectable <strong>keys</strong> are <strong>grid</strong>/<strong>middleware</strong> specific (defined by the <strong>radio button</strong> called <strong>Type</strong> on the <strong>Job Executable</strong> form)&nbsp; and the <strong>value</strong> part of the definition is a free string.&nbsp; However these free strings must correspond to the specifications of the respecting&nbsp; <em>job description languages</em>, i.e. the syntax check will be postponed to the job submission time. <br /></span></p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana\"><p><br /><em>Experienced users may notice that it is the portal Administrator who can define new keys to a given middleware in an XML configuration file.</em></p></span><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana\">To add an <strong>entry</strong> the user selects the <strong>key</strong> from the <strong>check list</strong> and defines the proper <strong>value</strong> in the input text field and finally confirms the definition by clicking on the <strong><em>Add</em></strong> button.<br /><br />The deletion is executed the same way: the <strong>entry</strong> is added repeatedly but this time with an empty string as <strong>value</strong>.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana\">Please remember that the closing of the JDL/RSL settings of the <strong>job</strong> does not ensures the saving/updating of the <strong>workflow</strong> in itself:<br />The user must hit the <strong>Save on Server</strong> button in the parent window before leaving the workflow configuration form. <br /></span></p>'),('help.history','HelpTextTab_JobHistory','<p><strong>Job history</strong> is a logbook where the <strong>time stamped</strong> changes of the configuration of the given <strong>job</strong> are recorded and displayed. <br /><br />The logbook is backed by an SQL database.<br /><br />The logbook is a sequence of<strong> items</strong> which are listed in time descending order.<br /><br />Every item is headed by a <strong>time stamp</strong> and lists the <strong>changed parts</strong>. The time stamp shows the time of the user command execution event when the workflow containing the given job had been saved to the server (with the  <strong><em>Save on Server</em></strong> button) <br /><br />Only the changed <strong>configuration parameters</strong> will be listed, identified by the following fields:</p><ul><li><strong>user:</strong> name of the user. This field will be the same for each parameter of the given entry</li><li><strong>port:</strong> port number - when applicable i.e. the parameter belongs to a given port</li><li><strong>key:</strong> internal identifier of the job level or port level based parameter</li><li><strong>old value:</strong>&nbsp; old value of the parameter (if any)</li><li><strong>new value:</strong> changed value of the parameter at the stamped time.</li></ul><p>The usage of the logbook is restricted by the fact that the prehistory of the <strong><em>uploaded</em></strong> or <strong><em>imported</em></strong> workflows are not preserved at the moment.<br />Consequently the name appearing in the field &ldquo;<strong>user</strong>&rdquo; must be identical with the name of the user just being logged in to the portal.&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>'),('error.job.mainnoconfig','WF info ErrMess_mainnoconfig','<p>Nothing in the set relating the job execution model of <strong>Binary</strong> type&nbsp; has been defined</p>'),('error.inputport.noconfig','WF info ErrMess_inputPort_noConfig','Nothing in the set relating the given input port has been defined'),('error.outputport.noconfig','WF info ErrMess_outPort_noConfig','<p>Output port is not configured</p>'),('error.job.proxyexpired','WF info ErrMess_ProxyExpired','<p>Proxy certificate has expired</p>'),('error.job.noproxy','WF info ErrMess_NoProxy','<p>No proxy certificate has been associated to the destination&nbsp;Grid of the Job execution</p>'),('error.executejob.resource','WF info ErrMess_NoResource','<p>No destination&nbsp;resource has been defined for job execution</p>'),('error.executejob.binary','WF info ErrMess_binaryExecutable','<p>No <strong>binary</strong> executable&nbsp;has been defined to the job</p>'),('help._wfimonitor_WAR_portal30_','HelpTextTab_WorkflowInfo','<p>The page Info opened by the <strong><em>Info</em></strong> button reveals the eventually found &ldquo;syntactical&rdquo; errors of a workflow. These errors fall in two categories:<br /></p><ol><li>There is no living (not expired) proxy certificate associated to the named <strong>job</strong>.</li><li>An obligatory configuration parameter within a <strong>job</strong> is missing.</li></ol><p><br />There is a separate line for each found error, and the corresponding item&nbsp; has three fields:</p><ul><li><strong>Job name</strong> : <br />locating the place of error within the workflow</li><li><strong>Port Number / *: <br /></strong>Auxiliary information, if necessary. <br />It may be for example the <strong>port number</strong> to locate a port if the error belongs to a given port, or the <strong>name of the Grid </strong>in case of certification problem </li><li><strong>Error:</strong>&nbsp; <br />Detailed description of the error&nbsp;&nbsp; </li></ul>'),('error.workflowjob.iworkflow','WF info ErrMess_Embedded','Embedded workflow not defined'),('error.servicejob.servicetype','WF info ErrMess_Service_type','The job execution model is a Service call but the service type is not defined'),('rror.servicejob.serviceurl','WF info ErrMess_Service_url',' The job execution model is a Service call but the service URL is not defined'),('error.servicejob.servicemethod','WF info ErrMess_Service_method','The job execution model is a Service call but the method is not defined'),('text.job.model','Config_job_model','Job execution model:'),('error.executejob.gridtype','WF info ErrMess_Binary_GridType','The job execution model is a <strong>Binary</strong> but the <strong>Type</strong> is not defined'),('error.executejob.gridtype','WF info ErrMess_Binary_Grid','The job execution model is a <strong>Binary</strong> but the <strong>Grid</strong> is not defined'),('error.executejob.resource','WF info ErrMess_Binary_Resource','The job execution model is a <strong>Binary</strong> but the <strong>Resource</strong> is not defined'),('error.executejob.jobmanager','WF info ErrMess_Binary_Jobmanager','The job execution model is a <strong>Binary</strong> but the <strong>Jobmanager</strong> is not defined'),('error.executejob.nodenumber','WF info ErrMess_Binary_NodeNumber','The job execution model is an <strong>MPI Binary</strong> but the <strong>Node number</strong> is not defined'),('error.inputport.noconfig','WF info ErrMess_InputPort_intname','<strong>Internal file name</strong> of the given input port has not been defined'),('error.inputport.file','WF info ErrMess_InputPort_UplodFile','<strong>The name of the file</strong> to be uploaded has not been defined'),('error.inputport.remote','WF info ErrMess_InputPort_RemoteFile','The name of <strong>the remote file</strong> to the given input port has not been defined'),('error.inputport.value','WF info ErrMess_InputPort_value','The <strong>Value</strong> to the given input port has not been defined'),('error.inputport.sqlurl','WF info ErrMess_SQL_URL','<strong>URL of the SQL</strong> database to the input port has not been defined'),('error.inputport.sqlselect','WF info ErrMess_InputPort_SQL_Select','The <strong>Select</strong> to the <strong>SQL</strong> database delivering values to the input port has not been defined'),('error.inputport.sqluser','WF info ErrMess_InputPort_SQL_User','The <strong>User</strong> of the <strong>SQL</strong> database delivering values to the input port has not been defined'),('error.inputport.sqlpass','WF info ErrMess_InputPort_SQL_Passw','The <strong>Password</strong> of the <strong>SQL</strong> database delivering values to the input port has not been defined'),('error.outputport.intname','WF info ErrMess_OutputPort_intName','The <strong>Internal file name</strong> of the given output port has not been defined'),('error.outputport.maincount','WF info ErrMess_OutputPort_GenerNum','The <strong>Generator number</strong> of the given output port has not been defined'),('error.outputport.ioutput','WF info ErrMess_OutputPort_RemoteFile','Name of the <strong>Remote file</strong> to the given output port has not been defined'),('help.templatelist','HelpTextTab_Template_Intro','<span style=\"font-size: 11pt; color: black; font-family: Verdana\"><p><strong>I. Introduction:<br /></strong>The term <strong>Template</strong> is the main abstraction in the gUSE to support the re-usability of the workflows. </p><p>Shortly speaking a <strong>Template</strong> is a generic <strong>Workflow</strong> where some configuration parameters are fixed permanently, so when a <strong>Template</strong> will be used to define a new <strong>Workflow</strong> the user will be helped substantially by inheriting the knowledge frozen in the (hopefully tested) <strong>Template</strong> and being not able to spoil the safe settings.<br />The lifecycle of a <strong>Template</strong> includes two main phases:</p><ol><li>Creating a newly named <strong>Template</strong> from a <strong>Workflow</strong> considered to be &ldquo;good&rdquo;.(This activity is done on the <strong><em>Workflow/Template</em></strong>) tab</li><li>Applying the <strong>Template</strong> to create a new <strong>Workflow</strong>.(By selecting the &ldquo;<em><strong>Template</strong></em>&rdquo; from the selectable list &ldquo;<strong>Create a workflow from a</strong>&rdquo;&nbsp; on the <strong><em>Workflow/Create Concrete</em></strong> tab)</li></ol><p>It must be noticed that for safety reasons only <strong>Workflows</strong> which have been created from <strong>Templates</strong> can be used as <strong>embedded workflows</strong>.&nbsp; (As you may see, only this kind of <strong>Workflow</strong> can be selected in the <strong>Job configuration</strong> if the <strong>Job execution model is</strong> set to &ldquo;<strong><em>Interpretation of the job as a Workflow</em></strong>&rdquo; )</p><p><strong>II.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Workflow/Template</strong> tab<br />The existing <strong>Templates</strong> are listed and maintained in the <strong><em>Workflow/Template</em></strong> tab, also the creation of a new <strong>Template</strong> can be initialized here as well.<br /><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><ol><li><strong>Template creation<br /><br />1.1</strong>The starting point is an existing <strong>Workflow</strong>. This <strong>Workflow</strong> can be created by the help of a different <strong>Template</strong> (lets name it &ldquo;<em><strong>Ancestor Template</strong></em>&rdquo;). In an even more special case we may want to reserve all fixed settings of the &ldquo;<strong><em>Ancestor Template</em></strong>&rdquo;. <br /><strong>-</strong> This operation is called <strong>derivation</strong> and can be chosen by selecting the <strong>radio button setting</strong> &ldquo;<strong>Select a templated concrete workflow as base to derive a template</strong>&rdquo;. <br />- In the alternate case the user selects one from the full set of Workflows ( &ldquo;<strong>Select a concrete workflow as base to create a template</strong>&rdquo;). In the later configuration process any parameter can be freed or fixed according to the user&rsquo;s convenience and independently of the existence of an eventual &ldquo;<strong><em>Ancestor Template</em></strong>&rdquo;.<br /><br /><strong>1.2</strong> The created new template must have a distinguished name (At the moment &ndash;because of historical causes &ndash; <strong>Workflows</strong> and <strong>Templates</strong> have a shared name space ).This must be defined in the input field of the label <strong>Name of new template</strong>:<br /><br /><strong>1.3</strong> The hitting of the <strong> Configure</strong> button opens the form where all individual parameters of the base <strong>Workflow</strong> are listed and the unconfigured ones can be set.<br />Please note that the configuration must be confirmed by the &ldquo;<strong>Save</strong>&rdquo; button<br /><br /></li><li><strong>Template maintenance <br /></strong>Existing Templates can be<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - deleted from the portal server (<strong>Delete</strong> button)<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - downloaded (in a compressed file) from the portal server to the computer of the client (<strong>Download</strong> button). <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (Upload can be done in the Workflow/Upload tab.)&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - export in the <strong>Repository</strong> (<strong>Export</strong> button).<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;(Import can be done by anyone accessing the portal using the <strong><em>Workflow/Import</em></strong> tab). <br /><br />You may notice that there is no &ldquo;<strong>Edit</strong>&rdquo; operation to change the settings of a <strong>Template</strong>. <br />This is for safety reasons: not allowing the user to change a <strong>Template</strong> which have been used to create existing <strong>Workflows</strong>. <br /><br />However there is a workaround: <br /><br />Let be <strong>T1</strong> the <strong>Template</strong> to be &ldquo;changed&rdquo; and <strong>W_T1</strong> the <strong>Workflow</strong> created from this template.<br />Then during the creation of new template <strong>T2</strong> we apply <strong>W_T1</strong> as base - in the not derivation way. <br />If you want to rename <strong>T2</strong> to <strong>T1</strong> then you have to delete <strong>T1</strong> (certainly with all the referenced workflows including <strong>W_T1</strong>) and repeat the whole process for <strong>W_T2</strong> for the <strong>Workflow</strong> which had been created using <strong>T2</strong>. </li></ol></span>'),('text.ctemplate.close','Config_Template_closed','Close'),('text.ctemplate.closed','Config_Template_closed','Closed'),('text.ctemplate.inherit','Template Text Free Detailed Inherit','<p>Inherit from Job:</p>'),('text.ctemplate.label','Template Text Free Detailed Label','<p>Label:</p>'),('text.ctemplate.description','Template Text Free Detailed Description','<p>Description:</p>'),('help.cabs','HelpTextTab_Template_Configuration','<p>On this form all configuration elements of the associated <strong>Workflow</strong>&nbsp;are listed and the<strong> user</strong> may decide abut the <strong>closing</strong> (freezing) of each individual elements.</p><p>As default all element are set &ldquo;to be closed&rdquo;. </p><p>Individual elements can be set to be &ldquo;<strong>Free</strong>&rdquo; indicating that later users configuring the <strong>Workflows</strong> which have been generated from the current <strong>Template</strong> may change the value of the given element. However not each element can be &ldquo;<strong>Free</strong>&rdquo;-ed; elements had been closed in a previous <strong>Template</strong> from which the current <strong>Template</strong> had been &ldquo;derived&rdquo; preserve their &ldquo;<strong>Closed</strong>&rdquo; state.</p><p>The list contains three features for each element - displayed as columns:<br />- the locket status<br />&nbsp;&ldquo;<strong>Close</strong>&rdquo;/&rdquo;<strong>Free</strong>&rdquo;&nbsp; or &ldquo;<strong>Closed</strong>&rdquo; if the locked status can not be changed<br />- The <strong>job/port</strong> based symbolic identifier of the given element <br />&nbsp; as it appears in&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; the proper configuration. <br />- The value (or setting) of the given element.</p><p>If the user judges an element to be changeable by selecting the <strong>radio button</strong> &ldquo;<strong><em>Free</em></strong>&rdquo; three additional input fields appear, which &ndash;in given cases - may be filled:<br />- <strong>Inherit from Job</strong>:<br />- <strong>Label</strong>:<br />- <strong>Description</strong>:</p><p><strong>Label</strong> and <strong>Description</strong> can be filled for the notification of a subsequent&nbsp; &ldquo;<em><strong>Non advanced&rdquo; user</strong></em>:<br /><strong><em>Non advanced users</em></strong> do not build a <strong>Workflow</strong> the traditional way:<br />They use a <strong>Template</strong> to generate a single simplified <strong>Form</strong> where all parameters of the <strong>workflow</strong> to be built and requested to be defined by the <strong><em>non advanced user</em></strong> are listed. The application dependent <strong>Name</strong> and <strong>Description</strong> belonging to each requested input value of this <strong>Form</strong> can be prepared by defining the <strong>Label</strong> and the <strong>Description</strong> respectively.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />&ldquo;<strong>Inherit from Job</strong>&rdquo; is a short hand. If the user has defined &ldquo;<strong>Label</strong>&rdquo; and &ldquo;<strong>Description</strong>&rdquo; in a different <strong>job</strong> for the same field, and wants the texts associated to the &ldquo;<strong>Label</strong>&rdquo; and to the &ldquo;<strong>Description</strong>&rdquo; to be replicated here, then references the given<strong> job</strong>.&nbsp;&nbsp; </p><p>&nbsp;Do not forget to confirm the configuration by hitting the <strong>Save</strong> button! </p>'),('portal.ctemplate.binhjob','Config_Template_Inherit','<p>&ldquo;<strong>Inherit from Job</strong>&rdquo; is a short hand. If the user has defined &ldquo;<strong>Label</strong>&rdquo; and &ldquo;<strong>Description</strong>&rdquo; in a different<strong> job</strong> for the same field, and wants the texts associated to the &ldquo;<strong>Label</strong>&rdquo; and to the &ldquo;<strong>Description</strong>&rdquo; to be replicated here then references the given <strong>job</strong>.</p>'),('portal.ctemplate.blabel','Config_Template_Label','<p><strong>Label</strong> can be filled for the notification of a later &ldquo;<strong>Non advanced&rdquo; user</strong> when he/she will use the current Template as a base to generate a simplified <strong>Workflow definer form</strong> showing the remaining free parameters to be defined.</p>'),('portal.ctemplate.bdesc','Config_Template_Description','<p>The <strong>Description</strong> can be filled for the notification of a later <strong>&ldquo;Non advanced&rdquo; user</strong> when he/she will use the current <strong>Template</strong> as a base to generate a simplified <strong>Workflow definer Form</strong> explaining the usage of the remaining <strong>free</strong> parameters to be defined.</p>'),('portal.ctemplate.ilabel','Config_Template_Label_inp','<p>The <strong>Label</strong> can be filled for the notification of a later <strong>&ldquo;Non advanced&rdquo; user</strong> when he/she will use the current <strong>Template</strong> as a base to generate a simplified <strong>Workflow definer Form</strong> showing the remaining <strong>free</strong> parameters to be defined.</p>'),('portal.ctemplate.olabel','Config_Template_Label_out','<p>The <strong>Label</strong> can be filled for the notification of a later <strong>&ldquo;Non advanced&rdquo; user</strong> when he/she will use the current <strong>Template</strong> as a base to generate a simplified <strong>Workflow definer Form</strong> showing the remaining <strong>free</strong> parameters to be defined.</p>'),('portal.ctemplate.idesc','Config_Template_Description_Inp','<p>The <strong>Description</strong> can be filled for the notification of a later <strong>&ldquo;Non advanced&rdquo; user</strong> when he/she will use the current <strong>Template</strong> as a base to generate a simplified <strong>Workflow definer Form</strong> explaining the usage of the remaining <strong>free</strong> parameters to be defined.</p>'),('portal.ctemplate.odesc','Config_Template_Description_Out','<p>The <strong>Description</strong> can be filled for the notification of a later <strong>&ldquo;Non advanced&rdquo; user</strong> when he/she will use the current <strong>Template</strong> as a base to generate a simplified <strong>Workflow definer Form</strong> explaining the usage of the remaining <strong>free</strong> parameters to be defined.</p>'),('portal.ctemplate.iinhjob','Config_Template_Inherit_Inp','<p>&ldquo;<strong>Inherit from Job</strong>&rdquo; is a short hand. If the user has defined the &ldquo;<strong>Label</strong>&rdquo; and the &ldquo;<strong>Description</strong>&rdquo; in a different<strong> job</strong> for the same field, and wants the texts associated to the &ldquo;<strong>Label</strong>&rdquo; and to the &ldquo;<strong>Description</strong>&rdquo; to be replicated here then references the given <strong>job</strong>.</p>'),('portal.ctemplate.oinhjob','Config_Template_Inherit_Out','<p>&ldquo;<strong>Inherit from Job</strong>&rdquo; is a short hand. If the user has defined the &ldquo;<strong>Label</strong>&rdquo; and the &ldquo;<strong>Description</strong>&rdquo; in a different <strong>job</strong> for the same field, and wants the texts associated to the &ldquo;<strong>Label</strong>&rdquo; and to the &ldquo;<strong>Description</strong>&rdquo; to be replicated here then references the given <strong>job</strong>.</p>'),('help.descvalue','HelpTextTab_JobJdlRslValue','<p>Actual <em>values</em> of the <strong>JDL/RSL</strong> table with their proper <em>keys</em> are listed in the red framed table.<br />To redefine or delete an existing element </p><ol><li>select the proper key from the <strong>checklist <em>Command</em></strong></li><li>define the new value in the <strong>input text field <em>Value</em></strong> - in the case of deletion leave empty</li><li>hit the <strong><em>Add</em></strong> button</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Please remember that <strong>closing</strong> of the <strong>JDL/RSL</strong> settings of the job does not ensures the saving/updating of the workflow in itself:<br />The user must hit the <strong><em>Save on Server</em></strong> button in the parent window before leaving the workflow configuration.</p>'),('help.timing','HelpTextTab_Timing','<p>This form prepares the scheduled starting of the selected <strong>workflows</strong>. <br />Any <strong>workflow</strong> can be selected and any <strong>future time</strong> can be defined.<br />The selected <strong>workflow</strong> will be included in the <strong>set </strong>of <strong>workflows</strong> to be started by hitting the <strong><em>Add</em></strong> button. <br />The function &ldquo;<strong>Add</strong>&rdquo; does not investigates the correctness or the ability of the <strong>workflow</strong> to run.<br />This <strong>set</strong> is displayed as a list from which each element can be revoked by the proper <strong><em>Delete</em></strong> button.</p><p>The submission in the scheduled time happens in rather low level way:<br />It <em>is the responsibility of the user</em> that the automatically started application &ldquo;finds&rdquo; the necessary valid (not expired) <strong>proxy certificates</strong>.</p>'),('help.remoting','HelpTextTab_Remoting','<p>This page enables that a proper <em>remote client program</em> may start a selected <strong>workflow</strong> to run.<br /><br />1. <br />By the <strong>check list <em>Select a workflow</em></strong> an existing <strong>workflow</strong> can be selected in order to put it in the <strong>Event Listener Table</strong>.<br /><br />An external program of a <em>remote client</em> can awake the listener and trigger the submission of the defined <strong>workflow</strong>.<br />The listening works as a <strong>Web Service</strong>. The external program must use the <strong>WSDL</strong> protocol.<br /><br />To authorize the remote call a <em>secret alphanumerical</em> key must be defined in the <strong>input field <em>Define a Remote Key</em></strong>.<br />The remote process which awakes the listener to submit the requested <strong>workflow</strong> must identify itself by sending the same <strong>key</strong> which will be checked against the value stored here.</p><p>The selected workflow will be added to the Event Listener Table by hitting the <strong><em>Add to table</em></strong> button.<br /><br />2. The listening workflows are listed here as well.<br /><br />A <strong>workflow</strong> can be revoked from the list in a two step operation:</p><ul><li>the <strong><em>View Key</em></strong> button opens a new <em>pane</em>,</li><li>within the this <em>pane</em> the hitting of the <strong><em>Delete</em></strong> button completes the operation.<br /></li></ul><p><br />3. Please remember that it is the responsibility of the portal user that the <strong>workflow</strong>s have a valid (not expired) <strong>proxy certificate</strong> in the time of their submissions </p>'),('help.download','HelpTextTab_Download','<p>I. Introduction<br />This page enables the downloading of Workflows, Workflow instances or parts of them from the Portal Server to the user&rsquo;s computer.</p><p>The selected object will be downloaded in form of a single compressed file.</p><p>This format enables the current or a different user to upload a selected workflow later from a local archive to the Portal server using the Workflow/Upload tab.</p><p>The main differences between the Upload/Download and the Export/Import mechanisms are the following:</p><p>Upload/Download happens between the Portal server and the current user where Export/Import connects the user&rsquo;s storage area on the Portal Server with the Repository<br />which is shared and visible among all users.<br /></p><p>II. Details<br />The starting point of accessing the downloadable items is the list of existing workflows. </p><p>1. Instances<br />As several workflow instances may belong to a single workflow, the user may decide to download only the information which belongs to a single workflow.&nbsp; <br />These operations are grouped under the column labeled as &ldquo;Instances&rdquo;.<br />Having selected a single instance by its Identifier (where the list of Identifiers is the same as the list opened by Details button in the Workflow/Concrete tab) two operations can be selected: <br />By hitting the Get Outputs button just the local output files will be produced by the given workflow run and can be reached <br />By hitting the Get Instance button the whole workflow Instance (including local input files, local output files and log information of running) can be downloaded</p><p>2. Workflow<br />The other kind of download options refer to the whole workflow and are collected under the column labeled as &ldquo;Download actions&rdquo;. It means that the referenced parts of all workflow instances will be downloaded as well:</p><p>By hitting the &ldquo;Get All&rdquo; button all data belonging to the workflow will be downloaded.<br />By hitting the &ldquo;Get All but logs&rdquo; button all data but run time logging information will be downloaded.<br />By hitting the &ldquo;Get Inputs&rdquo; button the local input files of all instances can be downloaded<br />By hitting the &ldquo;Get Outputs&rdquo; button the local output files of all instances can be downloaded.</p>'),('help._localstorage_WAR_portal30_','HelpTextTab_Download','<p><strong>I. Introduction<br /></strong><br />This page enables the downloading of <strong>Workflows</strong>, <strong>Workflow instances</strong> or <strong>parts of them</strong> from the <strong>Portal Server</strong> to the <strong>user&rsquo;s computer</strong>.</p><p>The selected object will be downloaded in form of a single compressed file.</p><p>This format enables the current or a different user to upload a selected <strong>workflow</strong> later from a <strong>local archive</strong> to the <strong>Portal Server</strong> using the<strong><em>Workflow/Upload</em></strong> tab.</p><p>The main differences between the Upload/Download and the Export/Import mechanisms are the following:</p><p>Upload/Download happens between the Portal server and the current user where Export/Import connects the user&rsquo;s storage area on the Portal Server with the Repository<br />which is shared and visible among all users.</li></ul><p><strong>II. Details</strong></p><p><br />The starting point of accessing the downloadable items is the list of existing<strong> workflows</strong>. </p><p><strong>1. Instances<br />As several workflow instances may belong to a single workflow, the user may decide to download only the information which belongs to a single workflow.&nbsp; <br />These operations are grouped under the column labeled as &ldquo;Instances&rdquo;.<br />Having selected a single instance by its Identifier (where the list of Identifiers is the same as the list opened by Details button in the Workflow/Concrete tab) two operations can be selected:</p><ul><li>By hitting the Get Outputs button just the local output files will be produced by the given workflow run and can be reached</li><li>By hitting the Get Instance button the whole workflow Instance (including local input files, local output files and log information of running) can be downloaded</li></ul><p><strong>2. Workflow</strong></p><p>The other kind of download options refer to the whole workflow and are collected under the column labeled as &ldquo;Download actions&rdquo;. It means that the referenced parts of all workflow instances will be downloaded as well:</p><ul><li>By hitting the &ldquo;Get All&rdquo; button all data belonging to the workflow will be downloaded.</li><li>By hitting the <strong><em>get All but logs</em></strong> button all data but run time logging information will be downloaded.</li><li>By hitting the <strong><em>Get Inputs</em></strong> button the <strong>local input files</strong> of all <strong>instances</strong> can be downloaded.</li><li>By hitting the <strong><em>get Outputs</em></strong> button the <strong>local output files</strong> of all <strong>instances</strong> can be downloaded.</li></ul>'),('help._wfupload_WAR_portal30_','HelpTextTab_Upload','<p><strong> I. Introduction</strong></p><p>This page enables the <strong>uploading</strong> of <strong>Graphs</strong> of <strong>Templates</strong> or of <strong>Workflows</strong> from the <strong>user&rsquo;s computer</strong> to the <strong>Portal Server</strong>.</p><p>On the <strong>user&rsquo;s computer</strong> the object to be uploaded is stored in a single compressed file, ruled by the syntax determined by a preceding <strong>Download</strong> operation.&nbsp;</p><p>The inverse <strong>Download</strong> operation can be found at the <strong><em>Download</em></strong> button in case of <strong>Graphs</strong> (<strong> <em>Workflow/Graph</em> tab</strong>)and in case of a <strong>Template</strong> (<strong><em>Workflow/Template</em> tab</strong>). The <strong>buttons <em>get All</em></strong> and <strong><em>get All but logs</em></strong> can be found in case of <strong>Workflows</strong> (<strong><em>Workflow/Storage</em></strong> tab).<br /><br />The uploading of a <strong>Workflow </strong>automatically involves the uploading of the associated <strong>Graph</strong> and may involve the uploading of a <strong>Template</strong> if the given <strong>Workflow</strong> had been defined on the basis of a <strong>Template</strong>.</p><p>During the <strong>upload</strong> process the referenced <strong>Graph</strong>, <strong>Template</strong> and <strong>Workflow</strong> objects &ndash;if no extra measure is taken- will be stored with their <strong>original names</strong> among the other objects of their own types in the proper name spaces.</p><p>Name collisions are not permitted and the new objects with colliding names are refused.<br />To avoid name collisions the user has the option to change the proper (<strong>Graph</strong>, <strong>Template</strong>, and <strong>Workflow</strong>) <strong>names</strong> to be <strong>uploaded</strong>. </p><p><strong>II Details</strong></p><p>The <strong>name</strong> of the <strong>compressed file</strong> to be uploaded can be defined either by typing its path in the <strong>input field</strong> <strong><em>Local Archive</em></strong> or located by the <strong>file browser</strong> &ldquo;<strong><em>Browse</em></strong>&rdquo;. The operation must be confirmed by hitting the <strong><em>Upload</em></strong> button.</p><p>The optional renaming of the objects (done in the proper <strong>input fields</strong> <strong><em>New Graph name</em></strong>, <strong><em>New Template name</em></strong>, <strong><em>New concrete Workflow name</em></strong>) must be preceded by the settings of the proper <strong>check boxes</strong>. </p>'),('help._wfimport_WAR_portal30_','HelpTextTab_Import','<p><strong>I. Introduction</strong></p><p>This page shows (and permits further operations on) the selected segment of the <strong>Repository</strong> which is shared among the users of the <strong>gUSE WS-Portal</strong>.&nbsp; </p><p>Five different kind of objects can be distinguished and selected as a segment:</p><ul><li>Graph</li><li>Template</li><li>Workflow</li><li>Application</li><li>Project</li></ul><p>The term <strong>Application</strong> means the definition of a full and environment free, tested <strong>Workflow </strong>(which involves the definition(s) of the <strong>embedded Workflows</strong> i.e. transitive closure of reference sequences of them including <strong>Graphs</strong> and <strong>Templates</strong>)</p><p>The term <strong>Project</strong> means the &quot;under construction&quot; state of an <strong>Application</strong> i.e. it is not full and tested however it contains the definition(s) of the <strong>embedded workflow</strong>(s) if it is available.</p><p>The term <strong>Workflow</strong> involves the definition of its <strong>Graph</strong> and may involve the definition of a <strong>Template</strong> if the <strong>workflow</strong> has been defined on the base of that <strong>Template</strong>.</p><p>The objects of the <strong>Repository</strong> has been created by proper export operations (<strong><em>Export</em></strong> button) issued on the <strong><em>Workflow/Graph</em></strong>, <strong><em>Workflow/Template</em></strong> and <strong><em>Workflow/Concrete</em></strong> tabs respectively. It must be remembered that all of these objects have been created with optionally detailed comments which are readable here in the column labeled as &ldquo;<strong><em>Notes</em></strong>&rdquo;.<br />The next important point to mention is that the <strong>export</strong> command of the <strong><em>Workflow/Concrete</em></strong> is branching to export the <strong>workflow</strong> as a <strong>common workflow</strong>, or as an <strong>Application</strong> or as a <strong>Project</strong>.</p><p>The base operation on this page is the <strong>Import</strong> of the selected object. However only the administrator user, the &ldquo;<strong>root</strong>&rdquo; has the right to <strong>Delete</strong> a <strong>repository item</strong>.<br /><br /><strong>Importing</strong> means to save the copy of the selected object from the <strong>Repository</strong> to the properly allocated <strong>user&rsquo;s storage area</strong> on the <strong>Portal Server</strong>. <br /><br />During the <strong>Import</strong> process the referenced <strong>Graph</strong>, <strong>Template</strong> and <strong>Workflow</strong> objects &ndash;if no extra measure is taken- will be stored with their <strong>original names</strong> among the other objects of their own types in the proper name spaces.<br />Name collisions are not permitted and the new objects with colliding names are refused.<br />To avoid name collision the user has the option to change the proper (<strong>Graph</strong>, <strong>Template</strong>, and <strong>Workflow</strong>) names of the object to be imported.</p><p>It is important to note that the <strong>embedded objects</strong> cause no name collision as their names will be automatically extended upon import in order to make them unique in the given name spaces.</p><p><br /><strong>II. Details</strong></p><p>The user activity includes 3 subsequent steps:</p><ol><li>Select the required <strong>Repository segment</strong> in the <strong>check list <em>Select type</em></strong> and confirm it with the <strong><em>Refresh/Show list</em></strong> button.</li><li>Select the object to be manipulated with the left side radio button. This step may include the optional prescription of <strong>renaming</strong> of the imported objects (done in the given <strong>input fields</strong> <strong><em>New Graph name</em></strong>, <strong><em>New Template name</em></strong>, <strong><em>New concrete Workflow name</em></strong> ) which must be preceded by setting of the proper <strong>check boxes</strong>.</li><li>To select the command to be executed choose from the <strong>check list <em>Select action type</em></strong> and confirm it with the <strong><em>Execute</em></strong> button.</li></ol>'),('help.jobinstances','HelpTextTab_JobInstances','<p>On this level the log and output files of a job instance can be reached by the </p><ul><li><em><strong>Logbook,</strong></em></li><li><em><strong>std. Output,</strong></em></li><li><em><strong>std. Error,</strong></em></li><li><em><strong>Download file output</strong></em> buttons,</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>where the <em><strong>file output</strong></em> is a compressed file containing the <strong>local output files</strong> generated by the current run of the<strong> job</strong>.</p><p>The <strong>job instances</strong> are identified and listed with the following features:</p><ul><li><em><strong>PID </strong></em>identifies the&nbsp; instance of the <strong>job</strong> which&nbsp; may be different from 0 in a<strong> Parameter Sweep</strong> running environment.</li><li><em><strong>Resource</strong></em> indicates the place where the job runs. Its content is <strong>submitter </strong>dependent and it may identify - for example - a <strong>Computing Element</strong> in case of <strong>job</strong> submissions of <strong>LCG2</strong> or <strong>gLite</strong> type.</li><li><em><strong>Status</strong></em> informs about the current run time state of the <strong>job</strong> where the values of the state are <strong>submitter</strong> dependent but include the states <strong>init</strong>, <strong>submitted</strong>, <strong>finished</strong>,<strong> error</strong><br /></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>'),('text.realworkflowlist.application','WF_export_type_value_application','application&nbsp;'),('text.realworkflowlist.project','WF_export_type_value_project','project'),('text.realworkflowlist.concrete','WF_export_type_value_concrete','workflow'),('text.ctemplate.key.iworkflow','Config_Template_Name_of_Embedded','Name of embedded Workflow'),('text.notify.wfchg.type','On_Submit_Notify','Send e-mail in case'),('text.notify.wfchg.type.not','On_Submit_Notify_value_never','<strong>never</strong>'),('text.notify.wfchg.type.end','On_Submit_Notify_value_end','workflow stopped'),('text.notify.wfchg.type.chg','On_Submit_Notify_value_state_changed','workflow state changed'),('portal.notify.whchg.type','HelpTextTab_Start_Notification','The user may instruct the system to send notification(s) about given state changes, having been caused <u>indirectly</u> or <u>directly</u> by the submission of a <strong>workflow</strong>:<br /><br />1.The trespass of a threshold value relating the <strong>Storage</strong> quota of the user in the gUSE Server&nbsp; is referred as<u> indirect change</u> .<br /><br />2.Two kinds of <u>direct changes </u>from the point of view are distinguished:<br /><br /><ul><li>The <strong>workflow instance</strong> reaches an end state (&ldquo;<strong>finished</strong>&rdquo; or &ldquo;<strong>error</strong>&rdquo;) from&nbsp; where it may not be moved without manual user action.</li><li>The global state of the <strong>workflow instance</strong> has changed (for example from &quot;<strong>submitted</strong>&quot; to &quot;<strong>running</strong>&quot;, or&nbsp; from &quot;<strong>running</strong>&quot; to &quot;finished&quot; or to &quot;<strong>error</strong>&quot;)</li></ul><p>The notification prescription will be forwarded to the submissions of the embedded workflows as well. </p><p>Currently the only way of the notification is a sent e-mail message, where the recipient and the event dependent content of the message is set by the <strong><em>Workflow/Notify</em> </strong> tab<br /></p>'),('portal.notify.wfchg.type','HelpTextTab_Start_Notification','The user may instruct the system to send notification(s) about given state changes, having been caused <u>indirectly</u> or <u>directly</u> by the submission of a <strong>workflow</strong>:<br /><br />1.The trespass of a threshold value relating the <strong>Storage</strong> quota of the user in the gUSE Server&nbsp; is referred as<u> indirect change</u> .<br /><br />2.Two kinds of <u>direct changes </u>from the point of view are distinguished:<br /><br /><ul><li>The <strong>workflow instance</strong> reaches an end state (&ldquo;<strong>finished</strong>&rdquo; or &ldquo;<strong>error</strong>&rdquo;) from&nbsp; where it may not be moved without manual user action.</li><li>The global state of the <strong>workflow instance</strong> has changed (for example from &quot;<strong>submitted</strong>&quot; to &quot;<strong>running</strong>&quot;, or&nbsp; from &quot;<strong>running</strong>&quot; to &quot;finished&quot; or to &quot;<strong>error</strong>&quot;)</li></ul><p>The notification prescription will not be forwarded to the submissions of the embedded workflows. </p><p>Currently the only way of the notification is a sent e-mail message, where the recipient and the event dependent content of the message is set by the <strong><em>Workflow/Notify</em> </strong> tab</p>'),('text.easyworkflowlist.name','Easy_Label_Workflow_Names','Workflow name'),('text.easyworkflowlist.status','Easy_Label_Workflow_States','States'),('text.easyworkflowlist.action','Easy_Label_Actions','Actions'),('text.notify.email.settings','Notify_Label_General_Settins','<strong>e-mail general settings</strong>'),('text.notify.email.settings','Notify_Label_General_Permission','<strong>e-mail general settings</strong>'),('text.notify.email.enab','Notify_Label_General_Permission','Sending'),('text.notify.disable','Notify_value_disabled','<strong>disabled</strong>'),('text.notify.enable','Notify_value_enabled','<strong>enabled</strong>'),('text.notify.email.addr','Notify_Label_Adress','Recipient&#39;s address'),('text.notify.email.subj','Notify_Label_General_Subject','Subject of message'),('text.notify.wfchg.settings','Notify_Label_WF_StateChange','<strong>Message about change of Workflow state</strong>'),('text.notify.wfchg.enab','Notify_Label_WF_Permit','Sending in this case<strong> </strong>'),('text.notify.wfchg.mess','Notify_Label_WF_Message','Skeleton of message<strong> </strong>'),('text.notify.quota.settings','Notify_Label_Quota_Settings','<strong>Message about trespassing the threshold of Storage quota </strong>'),('text.notify.quota.enab','Notify_Label_Quota_Permit','Sending in this case<strong> </strong>'),('text.notify.quota.mess','Notify_Label_Quota_Message','Skeleton of message'),('button.save','Button_Save','Save settings'),('help._notify_WAR_portal30_','HelpTextTab_Notify','<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p><p><br />The user may instruct the system to send notification(s) about given state changes, having been caused i<u>ndirectly</u> or <u>directly</u> by the submission of a <strong>workflow</strong>:<br /><br />1.The trespass of a <strong>threshold value</strong> relating the <strong>Storage quota</strong> of the user in the <strong>gUSE Server</strong>&nbsp; is referred as <u>indirect</u> change .<br /><br />2.Two kinds of <u>direct </u>changes from the point of view are distinguished:<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The<strong> workflow instance</strong> reaches an end state (&ldquo;<strong>finished</strong>&rdquo; or &ldquo;<strong>error</strong>&rdquo;) from&nbsp; where it may not be moved without manual user action.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The global state of the <strong>workflow instance</strong> has changed (for example from &quot;<strong>submitted</strong>&quot; to &quot;<strong>running</strong>&quot;, or&nbsp; from &quot;<strong>running</strong>&quot; to &quot;<strong>finished</strong>&quot; or to &quot;<strong>error</strong>&quot;).</p><p><br />The notification prescription will not be forwarded to the submissions of the embedded workflows. </p><p>Currently the only way of the notification is a sent <strong>e-mail message</strong>.<br />The <strong><em>Workflow/Notify</em></strong> tab configuring these messages is structured the following way: <br /><br /><strong>I.</strong><br /><strong>&nbsp;e-mail general settings</strong>&nbsp; groups the base information needed to send an electronic mail involving&nbsp; the <strong>recipient&rsquo;s address</strong>, the <strong>subject</strong> of the message and the overall permission to send any letter. <br /><em>The interested reader may notice that the URL of the SMPT server needed to send the letter can be changed by the <strong>Administrator</strong> of the <strong>gUSE Portal</strong> via the proper entry of the file <strong>Services.properties</strong> </em><br /><br /><strong>II.</strong><br /><strong>Message about change of Workflow state</strong> is the editable skeleton of the letter sent in the case of an event of <u>direct</u> change category (see above).&nbsp; <br />The <strong>user</strong> has a further filter possibility to <strong>disable</strong> /<strong>enable</strong> these letters by the selecting the proper value of the checklist <strong>Sending in this case</strong>:<br /><br />As a summary the sending of a letter has five conditions controlled by the user:</p><ol><li>The proper e-mail address is set</li><li><strong>Sending</strong> is enabled</li><li><strong>Sending in this case</strong> is enabled</li><li>Upon submitting the workflow on the question &ldquo;<strong>Send e-mail in case</strong>&rdquo; the answer is not &ldquo;<strong>never</strong>&rdquo;</li><li>The event listened for has occurred</li></ol><p>&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />The content of the message is free editable in the text area <strong>Skeleton of the message</strong>.<br /><br />The substituting values of the eventual <strong>keys</strong> inserted in the text will be evaluated in the time of sending the letter.<br /><br />These keys and their meanings are the following:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>#now#&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Time stamp of event</li><li>#user#&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Owner of the <strong>workflow</strong> </li><li>#portal#&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; URL of the <strong>portal</strong></li><li>#workflow#&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Name of <strong>workflow</strong></li><li>#instance#&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Identifier of <strong>workflow instance</strong></li><li>#oldsatus#&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; State prior the event</li><li>#newsatus#&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; State caused by the event</li></ul><p><br /><strong>III.</strong><br /><strong>Message about trespassing the threshold of Storage quota</strong> is the editable skeleton of the letter sent in the case of an event of <u>indirect</u> change category (see above).<br />&nbsp; <br /><em>The interested reader may notice that a&nbsp; integer threshold value meaning a ratio of the<strong> Storage</strong> capacity allotted to the <strong>user</strong>&nbsp; by the <strong>Administrator</strong> of the <strong>gUSE Portal&nbsp;</strong> is set in a proper entry of the file <strong>PGradePortal.properties</strong>.</em><br /><br />It must be noted the system realizes the trespass with a &ndash; sometimes long &ndash; delay, as it investigates the user quotas periodically and not at any storage requirement.</p><p> Therefore the system is fairly permissive: It does not suspend any running <strong>workflow</strong> on quota trespassing exception. However it prohibits manual <strong>submitting</strong> or <strong>editing</strong> operations until the quota problem is solved.<br />The <strong>user </strong>has a further filter possibility to <strong>disable</strong> /<strong>enable</strong> these letters by the selecting the proper value of the checklist <strong>Sending in this case</strong>:<br /><br />As a summary the sending of a letter of this kind has four conditions controlled partly the user:</p><ol><li>The proper e-mail address is set</li><li><strong>Sending</strong> is enabled</li><li><strong>Sending in this case</strong> is enabled</li><li>The quota checker&nbsp; has found threshold trespass.</li></ol><p><br />The content of the message is free editable in the text area <strong>Skeleton of the message</strong>.<br />The substituting values of the eventual <strong>keys</strong> inserted in the text will be evaluated in the time of sending the letter.<br />These <strong>keys</strong> and their meanings are the following:</p><ul><li>#now#&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; Time stamp of event</li><li>#user#&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Owner of the <strong>workflow</strong> </li><li>#portal#&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; URL of the <strong>portal</strong></li><li>#quota#&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Storage</strong> allotted by the <strong>Administrator</strong> to the <strong>user</strong> in the t<strong>ab <em>Workflow/settings</em></strong></li><li>#usedquota#&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Actual storage occupied by the user</li><li>#quotapercentmax#&nbsp;&nbsp; The common threshold value expressed in percent</li><li>#quotapercent#&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The ratio of &quot;u<strong>sedquota</strong>&quot; and &quot;<strong>quota</strong>&quot; expressed in percent</li></ul><p><br /><strong>IV.</strong> </p><p>The settings must be saved hitting the <strong><em>Save settings</em> button<br /> </strong></p>'),('text.configure.uploadinp','Config_Job_Upload_Progress','<strong>Upload in progress...<br /> </strong>'),('text.configure.uploadsuc','Config_Job_Upload_Termi','<strong>Upload terminated successfully! </strong>'),('text.configure.uploadstat','Config_Job_Upload_State','<strong>State of upload process<br /> </strong>'),('portal.NotifyPortlet.doSave.notvalid.addr','Java_Nofify_no_valid_malilAddress','<strong>e-mail address is not valid! Save is refused </strong>'),('portal.NotifyPortlet.default.wfchg.mess','Message_default_on_stat